{"type":"text","timestamp":1778636710814,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdfad4ffeSaQDXzGOm6pkom","part":{"id":"prt_e1f02632a001W7ZaeWDPYX6ot1","messageID":"msg_e1f0229d3001n06nAgcbZLecpK","sessionID":"ses_1e0fdfad4ffeSaQDXzGOm6pkom","type":"text","text":"The prior `micro_opt` attempt failed from implementation side effects, not because the source-use gating idea was invalid. I’m writing a narrower hypothesis that keeps raw IF/ID register fields intact for RVFI/cosim and uses source-use bits only inside the load-use stall predicate.","time":{"start":1778636710698,"end":1778636710813},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_003de174b558e576016a03d7a69750819b8a0f063ae52d50b9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636716168,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdfad4ffeSaQDXzGOm6pkom","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YjyBtwqIuyA4oaKVUMaHSdVK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Gate false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The pipeline currently stalls on any bit-pattern match between a load in\n+  ID/EX and the raw rs1/rs2 fields of the following IF/ID instruction. Many\n+  RV32I encodings do not actually consume both fields: OP-IMM and LOAD use\n+  only rs1, LUI/AUIPC/JAL use neither, and SYSTEM/FENCE are source-free for\n+  this core. These false dependencies inject bubbles in CoreMark's immediate\n+  arithmetic, loop setup, and address-update code without improving\n+  correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny opcode/funct3 source-use predecode feeding only the load-use\n+  hazard predicate. The hazard unit should compare the preceding load's rd\n+  against rs1 only when the next instruction actually reads rs1, and against\n+  rs2 only when it actually reads rs2. Keep the raw instruction rs1/rs2 fields\n+  flowing through ID/EX and RVFI unchanged so cosim still observes the required\n+  architectural register addresses and pre-write snapshots. This should recover\n+  otherwise wasted single-cycle bubbles with minimal new logic and little Fmax\n+  risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the raw rs1/rs2 load-use match with source-use-qualified matches derived from the IF/ID instruction opcode, preserving true load-use stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the full IF/ID instruction or explicit source-use qualifiers into the hazard unit without changing ID-stage raw register capture or RVFI fields.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Gate false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The pipeline currently stalls on any bit-pattern match between a load in\n+  ID/EX and the raw rs1/rs2 fields of the following IF/ID instruction. Many\n+  RV32I encodings do not actually consume both fields: OP-IMM and LOAD use\n+  only rs1, LUI/AUIPC/JAL use neither, and SYSTEM/FENCE are source-free for\n+  this core. These false dependencies inject bubbles in CoreMark's immediate\n+  arithmetic, loop setup, and address-update code without improving\n+  correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny opcode/funct3 source-use predecode feeding only the load-use\n+  hazard predicate. The hazard unit should compare the preceding load's rd\n+  against rs1 only when the next instruction actually reads rs1, and against\n+  rs2 only when it actually reads rs2. Keep the raw instruction rs1/rs2 fields\n+  flowing through ID/EX and RVFI unchanged so cosim still observes the required\n+  architectural register addresses and pre-write snapshots. This should recover\n+  otherwise wasted single-cycle bubbles with minimal new logic and little Fmax\n+  risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the raw rs1/rs2 load-use match with source-use-qualified matches derived from the IF/ID instruction opcode, preserving true load-use stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Pass the full IF/ID instruction or explicit source-use qualifiers into the hazard unit without changing ID-stage raw register capture or RVFI fields.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,28 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n+title: \"Gate false load-use stalls\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The pipeline currently stalls on any bit-pattern match between a load in\n+  ID/EX and the raw rs1/rs2 fields of the following IF/ID instruction. Many\n+  RV32I encodings do not actually consume both fields: OP-IMM and LOAD use\n+  only rs1, LUI/AUIPC/JAL use neither, and SYSTEM/FENCE are source-free for\n+  this core. These false dependencies inject bubbles in CoreMark's immediate\n+  arithmetic, loop setup, and address-update code without improving\n+  correctness.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a tiny opcode/funct3 source-use predecode feeding only the load-use\n+  hazard predicate. The hazard unit should compare the preceding load's rd\n+  against rs1 only when the next instruction actually reads rs1, and against\n+  rs2 only when it actually reads rs2. Keep the raw instruction rs1/rs2 