{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636722763,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdfad4ffeSaQDXzGOm6pkom","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JuyByOoJX06JRBp2d7dqF7fy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\n2: title: \"Gate false load-use stalls\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The pipeline currently stalls on any bit-pattern match between a load in\n6:   ID/EX and the raw rs1/rs2 fields of the following IF/ID instruction. Many\n7:   RV32I encodings do not actually consume both fields: OP-IMM and LOAD use\n8:   only rs1, LUI/AUIPC/JAL use neither, and SYSTEM/FENCE are source-free for\n9:   this core. These false dependencies inject bubbles in CoreMark's immediate\n10:   arithmetic, loop setup, and address-update code without improving\n11:   correctness.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Add a tiny opcode/funct3 source-use predecode feeding only the load-use\n14:   hazard predicate. The hazard unit should compare the preceding load's rd\n15:   against rs1 only when the next instruction actually reads rs1, and against\n16:   rs2 only when it actually reads rs2. Keep the raw instruction rs1/rs2 fields\n17:   flowing through ID/EX and RVFI unchanged so cosim still observes the required\n18:   architectural register addresses and pre-write snapshots. This should recover\n19:   otherwise wasted single-cycle bubbles with minimal new logic and little Fmax\n20:   risk.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 3\n23:   confidence: medium\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n26:     description: \"Replace the raw rs1/rs2 load-use match with source-use-qualified matches derived from the IF/ID instruction opcode, preserving true load-use stalls.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n28:     description: \"Pass the full IF/ID instruction or explicit source-use qualifiers into the hazard unit without changing ID-stage raw register capture or RVFI fields.\"\n\n(End of file - total 28 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260512-001-r2s0\ntitle: \"Gate false load-use stalls\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The pipeline currently stalls on any bit-pattern match between a load in\n  ID/EX and the raw rs1/rs2 fields of the following IF/ID instruction. Many\n  RV32I encodings do not actually consume both fields: OP-IMM and LOAD use\n  only rs1, LUI/AUIPC/JAL use neither, and SYSTEM/FENCE are source-free for\n  this core. These false dependencies inject bubbles in CoreMark's immediate\n  arithmetic, loop setup, and address-update code without improving\n  correctness.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a tiny opcode/funct3 source-use predecode feeding only the load-use\n  hazard predicate. The hazard unit should compare the preceding load's rd\n  against rs1 only when the next instruction actually reads rs1, and against\n  rs2 only when it actually reads rs2. Keep the raw instruction rs1/rs2 fields\n  flowing through ID/EX and RVFI unchanged so cosim still observes the required\n  architectural register addresses and pre-write snapshots. This should recover\n  otherwise wasted single-cycle bubbles with minimal new logic and little Fmax\n  risk.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-001-r2s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778636722755,"end":1778636722761}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_035ae3cc5585d2f7016a03d7b196e48198a1cf2f23e9f5ec74"}},"id":"prt_e1f028e10001PB4H0SVatubIIu","sessionID":"ses_1e0fdfad4ffeSaQDXzGOm6pkom","messageID":"msg_e1f0278c80027wE41uv0uB6CGZ"}}
