{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778636716716,"sessionID":"ses_1e0fdfa0affea77BgisF9SD2SE","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_uYDTyUAgt0rNZlpfIKfUUAla","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Resolve simple control flow in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline resolves every branch and jump in EX, so taken control\n+  flow still carries a two-stage wrong-path penalty unless the BTB predicts it\n+  correctly. The prior structural fetch skid buffer lost because it added IF\n+  control and muxing without shortening a common dependency path. CoreMark has\n+  many loop branches and unconditional jumps, so structurally moving simple\n+  target/condition resolution one stage earlier can improve iterations/cycle\n+  without widening retirement or adding front-end buffering.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an early-control path in ID for JAL and branch instructions whose operands\n+  are already available from the regfile or WB write-first bypass, and redirect\n+  IF before the instruction reaches EX. ID/EX should carry an early-resolved\n+  next PC plus a flag so EX can skip reissuing the same redirect while still\n+  preserving the existing EX resolution for forwarded operands, load-use cases,\n+  JALR, misalignment traps, and predictor updates. This reduces taken JAL and\n+  many non-dependent loop branch penalties by one cycle while keeping the\n+  single-retire RVFI boundary and trap discipline unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add ID/EX metadata for an early-resolved next PC and whether EX should suppress a duplicate redirect.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute JAL targets and safe branch outcomes in ID from regfile/WB-visible operands, exposing an early redirect only when no EX/MEM forwarding is required.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Honor ID early-control metadata so EX validates PC/RVFI state and predictor updates without redirecting twice.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire early ID redirect signals into the IF redirect path while preserving EX redirect priority and the NRET=1 RVFI interface.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Flush the correct younger stages for an ID-stage redirect without changing load-use, imem stall, or dmem stall semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260512-002-r2s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260512-002-r2s1\n+title: \"Resolve simple control flow in ID\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline resolves every branch and jump in EX, so taken control\n+  flow still carries a two-stage wrong-path penalty unless the BTB predicts it\n+  correctly. The prior structural fetch skid buffer lost because it added IF\n+  control and muxing without shortening a common dependency path. CoreMark has\n+  many loop branches and unconditional jumps, so structurally moving simple\n+  target/condition resolution one stage earlier can improve iterations/cycle\n+  without widening retirement or adding front-end buffering.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add an early-control path in ID for JAL and branch instructions whose operands