{"type":"text","timestamp":1778662228535,"sessionID":"ses_1df7a4985ffeVHT1KdBBh3XiCN","part":{"id":"prt_e2087c084001FYFBs74rl19Seq","messageID":"msg_e20864e03001JWChJMPQMJzMaz","sessionID":"ses_1df7a4985ffeVHT1KdBBh3XiCN","type":"text","text":"The prior winning pattern is local datapath/state reduction with unchanged behavior. I’m choosing a divider datapath consolidation: it mirrors the successful multiplier consolidation but avoids the earlier failed multi-cycle divider sidecar’s global stall/control cost.","time":{"start":1778662228100,"end":1778662228533},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0c6f807407c98532016a043b53f914819a89317364c4b489cc","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778662250997,"sessionID":"ses_1df7a4985ffeVHT1KdBBh3XiCN","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_bUixFS0vAh6SgMPlOKuzpw4L","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Share DIV/REM datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU case describes separate signed and unsigned division and remainder\n+  operators for DIV, DIVU, REM, and REMU. Even if CoreMark does not execute many\n+  divisions, these wide combinational operators can still consume LUTs and routing\n+  budget in the EX-stage ALU cone. The successful multiplier consolidation showed\n+  that preserving behavior while sharing expensive RV32M arithmetic can improve\n+  Tang Nano 20K fitness without adding pipeline control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the four DIV/REM operator expressions with one shared unsigned quotient\n+  and remainder datapath. For signed DIV/REM, form absolute-value operands, run the\n+  same unsigned divide/modulo hardware, then apply the RISC-V sign and overflow\n+  rules at the output; DIVU/REMU use the same raw quotient/remainder directly.\n+  Keep the operation combinational, leave RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions\n+  unchanged, and preserve all divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 semantics. This should\n+  reduce ALU area and mux pressure without introducing the stall/control overhead\n+  that made the prior divider sidecar regress.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Consolidate DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU onto a shared unsigned quotient/remainder datapath with signed pre/post-processing while preserving ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or extend RV32M divide/remainder edge vectors covering divide-by-zero, INT_MIN/-1, signed signs, and unsigned cases for the shared datapath.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Share DIV/REM datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU case describes separate signed and unsigned division and remainder\n+  operators for DIV, DIVU, REM, and REMU. Even if CoreMark does not execute many\n+  divisions, these wide combinational operators can still consume LUTs and routing\n+  budget in the EX-stage ALU cone. The successful multiplier consolidation showed\n+  that preserving behavior while sharing expensive RV32M arithmetic can improve\n+  Tang Nano 20K fitness without adding pipeline control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the four DIV/REM operator expressions with one shared unsigned quotient\n+  and remainder datapath. For signed DIV/REM, form absolute-value operands, run the\n+  same unsigned divide/modulo hardware, then apply the RISC-V sign and overflow\n+  rules at the output; DIVU/REMU use the same raw quotient/remainder directly.\n+  Keep the operation combinational, leave RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions\n+  unchanged, and preserve all divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 semantics. This should\n+  reduce ALU area and mux pressure without introducing the stall/control overhead\n+  that made the prior divider sidecar regress.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Consolidate DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU onto a shared unsigned quotient/remainder datapath with signed pre/post-processing while preserving ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or extend RV32M divide/remainder edge vectors covering divide-by-zero, INT_MIN/-1, signed signs, and unsigned cases for the shared datapath.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r10s0\n+title: \"Share DIV/REM datapath\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU case describes separate signed and unsigned division and remainder\n+  operators for DIV, DIVU, REM, and REMU. Even if CoreMark does not execute many\n+  divisions, these wide combinational operators can still consume LUTs and routing\n+  budget in the EX-stage ALU cone. The successful multiplier consolidation showed\n+  that preserving behavior while sharing expensive RV32M arithmetic can improve\n+  Tang Nano 20K fitness without adding pipeline control.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the four DIV/REM operator expressions with one shared unsigned quotient\n+  and remainder datapath. For signed DIV/REM, form absolute-value operands, run the\n+  same unsigned divide/modulo hardware, then apply the RISC-V sign and overflow\n+  rules at the output; DIVU/REMU use the same raw quotient/remainder directly.\n+  Keep the operation combinational, leave RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions\n+  unchanged, and preserve all divide-by-zero and INT_MIN/-1 semantics. This should\n+  reduce ALU area and mux pressure without introducing the stall/control overhead\n+  that made the prior divider sidecar regress.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Consolidate DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU onto a shared unsigned quotient/remainder datapath with signed pre/post-processing while preserving ALTOPS behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or extend RV32M divide/remainder edge vectors covering divide-by-zero, INT_MIN/-1, signed signs, and unsigned cases for the shared datapath.\"\n","additions":27,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r10s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778662250989,"end":1778662250994}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c6f807407c98532016a043b547070819a9fcfab16331b5388"}},"id":"prt_e2087c237001YjPBwYa9BIUYbc","sessionID":"ses_1df7a4985ffeVHT1KdBBh3XiCN","messageID":"msg_e20864e03001JWChJMPQMJzMaz"}}
