{"type":"text","timestamp":1778664505713,"sessionID":"ses_1df5663b7ffecagKBrSvLsd6ps","part":{"id":"prt_e20aa7b340010DI53gmPLBWDr1","messageID":"msg_e20aa06eb001nzhtOXMAfJO0fy","sessionID":"ses_1df5663b7ffecagKBrSvLsd6ps","type":"text","text":"The prior wins favor behavior-preserving reductions in hot state/control width, while recent regressions came from predictor policy changes and RVFI/writeback restructuring. The most plausible remaining micro-opt is to keep BTB behavior unchanged but stop resetting predictor tag/target/counter arrays whose contents are masked by `btb_valid`.","time":{"start":1778664504116,"end":1778664505712},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_07212dbc0892eb9f016a04443801d481989a2c70b162b4363d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
