{"type":"text","timestamp":1778668514287,"sessionID":"ses_1df19de50ffexLDv6A7366ABy6","part":{"id":"prt_e20e7ab89001d10Av81agtZiXw","messageID":"msg_e20e6c920001GZNa139Ite7kVp","sessionID":"ses_1df19de50ffexLDv6A7366ABy6","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis now as a short-form `rtl/...` change list focused on reusing the existing PC+immediate datapath and deleting the separate AUIPC control payload.","time":{"start":1778668514185,"end":1778668514284},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06f21d454be19857016a0453e21360819a96bb2f294160b560","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778668535710,"sessionID":"ses_1df19de50ffexLDv6A7366ABy6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ZpjO58wK7LbRELT9ItRBBWIX","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Share PC-immediate result path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best recent bench-core wins came from local datapath isolation and payload pruning, especially keeping common CoreMark address/control operations away from the full RV32IM ALU mux. After the LSU-address bypass, AUIPC is still routed through the full ALU by carrying a dedicated is_auipc bit through every pipeline stage and muxing the ALU A operand between rs1 and pc.\n+\n+  CoreMark and the linked runtime still use pc-relative address formation around calls, constants, and data references, so AUIPC should share the already-required pc+imm target adder rather than keeping an extra control bit and ALU input mux pressure alive.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Reuse a single EX-stage pc+imm sum for branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC writeback. Encode AUIPC in the existing alu_op field with a new internal operation value, remove ctrl_t.is_auipc and its decoder/id-stage wiring, and make EX select the pc+imm result for that operation instead of feeding pc through the full ALU operand mux.\n+\n+  This preserves branch/jump redirect behavior, RVFI pc_wdata and rd_wdata, traps, forwarding, and the NRET=1 top-level contract while trimming one carried control bit and shortening the common ALU operand-select/result cone. The expected gain is mostly Fmax and routing pressure, with little cycle-count risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove ctrl_t.is_auipc and add an internal ALU_AUIPC opcode so AUIPC can be identified without carrying a separate pipeline control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Decode AUIPC by setting alu_op to ALU_AUIPC with reg_write enabled, while leaving LUI and other opcode legality checks unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the dec_is_auipc signal and ctrl_decoded.is_auipc assignment after the decoder no longer exposes that control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute one pc+imm sum and reuse it for branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC writeback, excluding AUIPC from the full ALU input mux path.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Share PC-immediate result path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best recent bench-core wins came from local datapath isolation and payload pruning, especially keeping common CoreMark address/control operations away from the full RV32IM ALU mux. After the LSU-address bypass, AUIPC is still routed through the full ALU by carrying a dedicated is_auipc bit through every pipeline stage and muxing the ALU A operand between rs1 and pc.\n+\n+  CoreMark and the linked runtime still use pc-relative address formation around calls, constants, and data references, so AUIPC should share the already-required pc+imm target adder rather than keeping an extra control bit and ALU input mux pressure alive.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Reuse a single EX-stage pc+imm sum for branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC writeback. Encode AUIPC in the existing alu_op field with a new internal operation value, remove ctrl_t.is_auipc and its decoder/id-stage wiring, and make EX select the pc+imm result for that operation instead of feeding pc through the full ALU operand mux.\n+\n+  This preserves branch/jump redirect behavior, RVFI pc_wdata and rd_wdata, traps, forwarding, and the NRET=1 top-level contract while trimming one carried control bit and shortening the common ALU operand-select/result cone. The expected gain is mostly Fmax and routing pressure, with little cycle-count risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove ctrl_t.is_auipc and add an internal ALU_AUIPC opcode so AUIPC can be identified without carrying a separate pipeline control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Decode AUIPC by setting alu_op to ALU_AUIPC with reg_write enabled, while leaving LUI and other opcode legality checks unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the dec_is_auipc signal and ctrl_decoded.is_auipc assignment after the decoder no longer exposes that control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute one pc+imm sum and reuse it for branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC writeback, excluding AUIPC from the full ALU input mux path.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r12s0\n+title: \"Share PC-immediate result path\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The best recent bench-core wins came from local datapath isolation and payload pruning, especially keeping common CoreMark address/control operations away from the full RV32IM ALU mux. After the LSU-address bypass, AUIPC is still routed through the full ALU by carrying a dedicated is_auipc bit through every pipeline stage and muxing the ALU A operand between rs1 and pc.\n+\n+  CoreMark and the linked runtime still use pc-relative address formation around calls, constants, and data references, so AUIPC should share the already-required pc+imm target adder rather than keeping an extra control bit and ALU input mux pressure alive.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Reuse a single EX-stage pc+imm sum for branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC writeback. Encode AUIPC in the existing alu_op field with a new internal operation value, remove ctrl_t.is_auipc and its decoder/id-stage wiring, and make EX select the pc+imm result for that operation instead of feeding pc through the full ALU operand mux.\n+\n+  This preserves branch/jump redirect behavior, RVFI pc_wdata and rd_wdata, traps, forwarding, and the NRET=1 top-level contract while trimming one carried control bit and shortening the common ALU operand-select/result cone. The expected gain is mostly Fmax and routing pressure, with little cycle-count risk.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove ctrl_t.is_auipc and add an internal ALU_AUIPC opcode so AUIPC can be identified without carrying a separate pipeline control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Decode AUIPC by setting alu_op to ALU_AUIPC with reg_write enabled, while leaving LUI and other opcode legality checks unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the dec_is_auipc signal and ctrl_decoded.is_auipc assignment after the decoder no longer exposes that control bit.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute one pc+imm sum and reuse it for branch targets, JAL targets, and AUIPC writeback, excluding AUIPC from the full ALU input mux path.\"\n","additions":23,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r12s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778668535705,"end":1778668535709}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06f21d454be19857016a0453e22978819a858f911879aaee02"}},"id":"prt_e20e7abed001ajKtAY8AyLjXDI","sessionID":"ses_1df19de50ffexLDv6A7366ABy6","messageID":"msg_e20e6c920001GZNa139Ite7kVp"}}
