{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778670769636,"sessionID":"ses_1def73698ffeM2YkNch3jE8WZx","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_YRobfH3lJYrXLlukhxeaDh8y","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n2: title: \"Separate jump predictor state\"\n3: category: predictor\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current compact 16-entry PC-only BTB with two-bit counters is still the\n6:   only predictor structure that has produced a durable CoreMark win. Recent\n7:   predictor attempts regressed when they changed table capacity, added\n8:   instruction-dependent fetch logic, filtered conditional feedback, delayed\n9:   updates, or added victim/RAS state. A safer remaining angle is to keep the\n10:   proven lookup geometry but avoid spending conditional-branch hysteresis logic\n11:   on unconditional jumps, which are always taken once their target is known.\n12: hypothesis: |\n13:   Add a per-BTB-entry unconditional-jump marker set by EX for JAL/JALR updates.\n14:   Fetch should predict a valid tag hit when either the entry is marked\n15:   unconditional or the existing two-bit conditional counter is taken; conditional\n16:   branches continue to use the same 2-bit counter policy and target storage.\n17:   The update path should write jump entries as always-taken target entries and\n18:   skip counter increment/decrement work for them, while branch entries keep the\n19:   current weak allocation and saturating training. This preserves the 16-entry\n20:   PC-only table, compact tags, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 contract, but may\n21:   trim predictor update pressure and reduce alias damage between calls/jumps and\n22:   conditional loop branches without adding IF-side instruction predecode.\n23: expected_impact:\n24:   fitness_delta_pct: 1\n25:   confidence: medium\n26: changes:\n27:   - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n28:     description: \"Add a per-entry unconditional marker to the existing 16-entry BTB and use it with the current counter MSB for PC-only prediction, while preserving tag, target, reset, and redirect behavior.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Classify BPU updates as unconditional for JAL/JALR versus conditional branches so IF can skip counter training for always-taken jump entries.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/core.sv\n32:     description: \"Wire the new unconditional-update bit from EX to IF without changing the single-channel RVFI or memory port contract.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\ntitle: \"Separate jump predictor state\"\ncategory: predictor\nmotivation: |\n  The current compact 16-entry PC-only BTB with two-bit counters is still the\n  only predictor structure that has produced a durable CoreMark win. Recent\n  predictor attempts regressed when they changed table capacity, added\n  instruction-dependent fetch logic, filtered conditional feedback, delayed\n  updates, or added victim/RAS state. A safer remaining angle is to keep the\n  proven lookup geometry but avoid spending conditional-branch hysteresis logic\n  on unconditional jumps, which are always taken once their target is known.\nhypothesis: |\n  Add a per-BTB-entry unconditional-jump marker set by EX for JAL/JALR updates.\n  Fetch should predict a valid tag hit when either the entry is marked\n  unconditional or the existing two-bit conditional counter is taken; conditional\n  branches continue to use the same 2-bit counter policy and target storage.\n  The update path should write jump entries as always-taken target entries and\n  skip counter increment/decrement work for them, while branch entries keep the\n  current weak allocation and saturating training. This preserves the 16-entry\n  PC-only table, compact tags, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 contract, but may","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778670769630,"end":1778670769635}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_05f78c227384552b016a045caf221c819ab58b711d9cc0a712"}},"id":"prt_e210a0c8f001Cjnqvi82oJzwG3","sessionID":"ses_1def73698ffeM2YkNch3jE8WZx","messageID":"msg_e2109f3e7001Ek1k4chaE7IJ63"}}
