{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778673196324,"sessionID":"ses_1ded295ccffe2WFpU86mR6hSm3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_PNm4sZUIhrugfybGr7HndeVd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Derive memory width in MEM\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline carries mem_width and mem_sext through every control\n+  bundle even though those bits are only consumed in the MEM stage and are\n+  already encoded in the instruction funct3 field that the pipeline carries\n+  for RVFI. Prior successful micro-opts reduced behavior-preserving payload\n+  width and local mux pressure, while recent regressions came from adding new\n+  hot fast-lane selects or reusing heavily fanned-out controls.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_width and ctrl_t.mem_sext from the decoded control payload\n+  and derive the access width and load signedness locally in rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+  from in.instr[14:12] when mem_read or mem_write is asserted. Legal LOAD and\n+  STORE encodings are already validated by the decoder before those controls\n+  are set, so reserved funct3 values still retire as illegal instructions with\n+  no memory request. This should trim three carried control bits from ID/EX,\n+  EX/MEM, and MEM/WB, reduce decoder and pipeline-register fanout, and keep\n+  the existing load formatting, store masks, misalignment traps, RVFI fields,\n+  and NRET=1 top-level contract unchanged.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove mem_width and mem_sext from ctrl_t so the memory-only format bits are no longer carried through every pipeline stage.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop driving mem_width and mem_sext outputs; keep LOAD/STORE legality checks and mem_read/mem_write/reg_write behavior unchanged.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove decoded memory width/sign wiring and ctrl_t assignments that only existed to transport funct3-derived memory format bits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Decode memory access width and load signedness locally from in.instr[14:12] for byte masks, load extension, and misalignment checks.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n+title: \"Derive memory width in MEM\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline carries mem_width and mem_sext through every control\n+  bundle even though those bits are only consumed in the MEM stage and are\n+  already encoded in the instruction funct3 field that the pipeline carries\n+  for RVFI. Prior successful micro-opts reduced behavior-preserving payload\n+  width and local mux pressure, while recent regressions came from adding new\n+  hot fast-lane selects or reusing heavily fanned-out controls.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_width and ctrl_t.mem_sext from the decoded control payload\n+  and derive the access width and load signedness locally in rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+  from in.instr[14:12] when mem_read or mem_write is asserted. Legal LOAD and\n+  STORE encodings are already validated by the decoder before those controls\n+  are set, so reserved funct