{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778673206721,"sessionID":"ses_1ded295ccffe2WFpU86mR6hSm3","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_iDgZakNSErri8lEllFLVSQAA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\n2: title: \"Derive memory width in MEM\"\n3: category: micro_opt\n4: motivation: |\n5:   The current pipeline carries mem_width and mem_sext through every control\n6:   bundle even though those bits are only consumed in the MEM stage and are\n7:   already encoded in the instruction funct3 field that the pipeline carries\n8:   for RVFI. Prior successful micro-opts reduced behavior-preserving payload\n9:   width and local mux pressure, while recent regressions came from adding new\n10:   hot fast-lane selects or reusing heavily fanned-out controls.\n11: hypothesis: |\n12:   Remove ctrl_t.mem_width and ctrl_t.mem_sext from the decoded control payload\n13:   and derive the access width and load signedness locally in rtl/mem_stage.sv\n14:   from in.instr[14:12] when mem_read or mem_write is asserted. Legal LOAD and\n15:   STORE encodings are already validated by the decoder before those controls\n16:   are set, so reserved funct3 values still retire as illegal instructions with\n17:   no memory request. This should trim three carried control bits from ID/EX,\n18:   EX/MEM, and MEM/WB, reduce decoder and pipeline-register fanout, and keep\n19:   the existing load formatting, store masks, misalignment traps, RVFI fields,\n20:   and NRET=1 top-level contract unchanged.\n21: expected_impact:\n22:   fitness_delta_pct: 3\n23:   confidence: medium\n24: changes:\n25:   - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n26:     description: \"Remove mem_width and mem_sext from ctrl_t so the memory-only format bits are no longer carried through every pipeline stage.\"\n27:   - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n28:     description: \"Stop driving mem_width and mem_sext outputs; keep LOAD/STORE legality checks and mem_read/mem_write/reg_write behavior unchanged.\"\n29:   - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n30:     description: \"Remove decoded memory width/sign wiring and ctrl_t assignments that only existed to transport funct3-derived memory format bits.\"\n31:   - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n32:     description: \"Decode memory access width and load signedness locally from in.instr[14:12] for byte masks, load extension, and misalignment checks.\"\n\n(End of file - total 32 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: hyp-20260513-001-r14s0\ntitle: \"Derive memory width in MEM\"\ncategory: micro_opt\nmotivation: |\n  The current pipeline carries mem_width and mem_sext through every control\n  bundle even though those bits are only consumed in the MEM stage and are\n  already encoded in the instruction funct3 field that the pipeline carries\n  for RVFI. Prior successful micro-opts reduced behavior-preserving payload\n  width and local mux pressure, while recent regressions came from adding new\n  hot fast-lane selects or reusing heavily fanned-out controls.\nhypothesis: |\n  Remove ctrl_t.mem_width and ctrl_t.mem_sext from the decoded control payload\n  and derive the access width and load signedness locally in rtl/mem_stage.sv\n  from in.instr[14:12] when mem_read or mem_write is asserted. Legal LOAD and\n  STORE encodings are already validated by the decoder before those controls\n  are set, so reserved funct3 values still retire as illegal instructions with\n  no memory request. This should trim three carried control bits from ID/EX,\n  EX/MEM, and MEM/WB, reduce decoder and pipeline-register fanout, and keep\n  the existing load formatting, store masks, misalignment traps, RVFI fields,\n  and NRET=1 top-level contract unchanged.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r14s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778673206714,"end":1778673206720}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0fb3cabf44b7ff6c016a0466355784819a8afbf8ea8d250fe6"}},"id":"prt_e212f40ca001GyEa1YcOAQ6Ori","sessionID":"ses_1ded295ccffe2WFpU86mR6hSm3","messageID":"msg_e212f1d6f001RNdMP0i80yqBzJ"}}
