{"type":"text","timestamp":1778675417050,"sessionID":"ses_1deb04bedffeTLzR5fcCq7oytJ","part":{"id":"prt_e2150f7b6001Q54m7qeCDLD0xo","messageID":"msg_e215000f0001JCLLCiGa3ikCqw","sessionID":"ses_1deb04bedffeTLzR5fcCq7oytJ","type":"text","text":"The strongest safe pattern is still behavior-preserving EX/MEM datapath trimming. I’m going to avoid the failed broad AUIPC/add fast-lane variants and propose a narrower EX-stage micro-opt: explicitly share the duplicated `pc + imm` adder used for branch and JAL targets only.","time":{"start":1778675414966,"end":1778675417047},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_050e351c431e7f89016a046ed6c15c8198a2c094b09caacf74","phase":"commentary"}}}}
