{"type":"text","timestamp":1778675426481,"sessionID":"ses_1deb04bedffeTLzR5fcCq7oytJ","part":{"id":"prt_e21512255001S4Qm1XfbVXiG66","messageID":"msg_e215109c4001DE4q1aAW3RO55M","sessionID":"ses_1deb04bedffeTLzR5fcCq7oytJ","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis file now with only `rtl/ex_stage.sv` in `changes`, since this should be a single local RTL change and not a multi-file structural rewrite.","time":{"start":1778675425877,"end":1778675426478},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02ec70d4b95e891b016a046ee1c4b4819b935ce1dae4ef3b51","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778675441172,"sessionID":"ses_1deb04bedffeTLzR5fcCq7oytJ","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_OgSl2Fxa2shywZIosh6W9VxO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Share branch and JAL target adder\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent wins for cores/bench came from small behavior-preserving reductions in EX-stage datapath width and fanout, while broader fast-lane and AUIPC rewrites regressed by adding new result selects or hot control compares. The current EX stage still computes the same pc+imm expression twice: once as branch_target and again as the non-JALR jump target. CoreMark has dense branch and call traffic, so removing a redundant 32-bit target adder may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing IPC, predictor behavior, RVFI, or stall semantics.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Introduce one shared pc_imm_sum in rtl/ex_stage.sv and use it for both conditional branch targets and direct JAL targets. Leave the existing JALR rs1+imm path, pc+4 link result, AUIPC/full-ALU path, predictor update semantics, misalignment trap handling, redirect priority, forwarding, and pipeline registers unchanged. This is deliberately narrower than the failed AUIPC pc-immediate sharing attempt: it removes only an actually duplicated EX expression and does not replace carried control bits or add a new writeback result mux.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a single pc_imm_sum for branch_target and non-JALR jump_target, preserving JALR, pc+4, redirects, predictor updates, and misalignment traps.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Share branch and JAL target adder\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent wins for cores/bench came from small behavior-preserving reductions in EX-stage datapath width and fanout, while broader fast-lane and AUIPC rewrites regressed by adding new result selects or hot control compares. The current EX stage still computes the same pc+imm expression twice: once as branch_target and again as the non-JALR jump target. CoreMark has dense branch and call traffic, so removing a redundant 32-bit target adder may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing IPC, predictor behavior, RVFI, or stall semantics.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Introduce one shared pc_imm_sum in rtl/ex_stage.sv and use it for both conditional branch targets and direct JAL targets. Leave the existing JALR rs1+imm path, pc+4 link result, AUIPC/full-ALU path, predictor update semantics, misalignment trap handling, redirect priority, forwarding, and pipeline registers unchanged. This is deliberately narrower than the failed AUIPC pc-immediate sharing attempt: it removes only an actually duplicated EX expression and does not replace carried control bits or add a new writeback result mux.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a single pc_imm_sum for branch_target and non-JALR jump_target, preserving JALR, pc+4, redirects, predictor updates, and misalignment traps.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r15s0\n+title: \"Share branch and JAL target adder\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent wins for cores/bench came from small behavior-preserving reductions in EX-stage datapath width and fanout, while broader fast-lane and AUIPC rewrites regressed by adding new result selects or hot control compares. The current EX stage still computes the same pc+imm expression twice: once as branch_target and again as the non-JALR jump target. CoreMark has dense branch and call traffic, so removing a redundant 32-bit target adder may improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing IPC, predictor behavior, RVFI, or stall semantics.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Introduce one shared pc_imm_sum in rtl/ex_stage.sv and use it for both conditional branch targets and direct JAL targets. Leave the existing JALR rs1+imm path, pc+4 link result, AUIPC/full-ALU path, predictor update semantics, misalignment trap handling, redirect priority, forwarding, and pipeline registers unchanged. This is deliberately narrower than the failed AUIPC pc-immediate sharing attempt: it removes only an actually duplicated EX expression and does not replace carried control bits or add a new writeback result mux.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Compute a single pc_imm_sum for branch_target and non-JALR jump_target, preserving JALR, pc+4, redirects, predictor updates, and misalignment traps.\"\n","additions":13,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r15s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778675441163,"end":1778675441170}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02ec70d4b95e891b016a046ee262e8819b84cb53d43021e9c6"}},"id":"prt_e215124b1001MIz3oSAyowL5Qv","sessionID":"ses_1deb04bedffeTLzR5fcCq7oytJ","messageID":"msg_e215109c4001DE4q1aAW3RO55M"}}
