{"type":"text","timestamp":1778642823079,"sessionID":"ses_1e0a1118dffebzt2ghRURgFtoL","part":{"id":"prt_e1f5fa625001c27EQAYe4R4v91","messageID":"msg_e1f5f8c6e002A3ybgE2XzsnXVl","sessionID":"ses_1e0a1118dffebzt2ghRURgFtoL","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a focused hypothesis for replacing the MEM-stage variable shift/multiply load formatter with explicit byte-lane muxes, preserving behavior while shortening the forwarding path.","time":{"start":1778642822693,"end":1778642823078},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_079158dbde540757016a03ef86961c819983a0ac8bff8ea5e9","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778642829628,"sessionID":"ses_1e0a1118dffebzt2ghRURgFtoL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_ly5WQoNRfhTRBifzC0lF4ZV0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Optimize load byte-lane formatter\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM stage formats byte and halfword loads with a variable\n+  32-bit right shift by addr[1:0] * 8, then forwards the formatted value\n+  directly into the EX-stage operand mux for load-dependent instructions.\n+  That creates a likely critical path from dmem read data through a barrel\n+  shifter, sign-extension mux, forwarding mux, and ALU/branch compare.\n+  CoreMark has frequent loads and dependent address/data use, so improving\n+  this path should raise FPGA Fmax without changing the single-retire IPC\n+  model or any architectural behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the variable-shift load extraction and shifted byte-mask logic in\n+  rtl/mem_stage.sv with explicit case statements keyed by alu_result[1:0].\n+  Select byte_val and hword_val directly from dmem_rdata lanes, generate the\n+  byte/half/word masks with small decode logic, and keep the existing\n+  misalignment trapping, RVFI aligned address reporting, and formatted\n+  MEM-stage forwarding semantics unchanged. This is a local micro-optimization\n+  intended to reduce LUT depth on the load-to-use forwarding path while\n+  preserving the current CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace variable shifts for load extraction and store masks with explicit addr[1:0] lane mux/decode logic while preserving RVFI and misalignment behavior.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r3s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,27 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r3s0\n+title: \"Optimize load byte-lane formatter\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current MEM stage formats byte and halfword loads with a variable\n+  32-bit right shift by addr[1:0] * 8, then forwards the formatted value\n+  directly into the EX-stage operand mux for load-dependent instructions.\n+  That creates a likely critical path from dmem read data through a barrel\n+  shifter, sign-extension mux, forwarding mux, and ALU/branch compare.\n+  CoreMark has frequent loads and dependent address/data use, so improving\n+  this path should raise FPGA Fmax without changing the single-retire IPC\n+  model or any architectural behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the variable-shift load extraction and shifted byte-mask logic in\n+  rtl/mem_stage.sv with explicit case statements keyed by alu_result[1:0].\n+  Select byte_val and hword_val directly from dmem_rdata lanes, generate the\n+  byte/half/word masks with small decode logic, and keep the existing\n+  misalignment trapping, RVFI aligned address reporting, and formatted\n+  MEM-stage forwarding semantics unchanged. This is a local micro-optimization\n+  intended to reduce LUT depth on the load-to-use forwarding path while\n+  preserving the current CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+