2 bits still implement MUL because\n+  signedness does not affect the low product half, while bits [63:32] provide\n+  MULH, MULHU, and MULHSU after choosing signed/signed, unsigned/unsigned, or\n+  signed/unsigned operands. Keep the existing DIV/REM logic and the\n+  RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS substitutions unchanged. This should reduce multiplier\n+  LUT/DSP fanout and ALU result mux pressure without changing pipeline timing,\n+  RVFI behavior, or CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Collapse the three parallel MUL-family products into a single signedness-selected 33x33 product while preserving ALTOPS and DIV/REM behavior.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Add or extend directed MULH/MULHU/MULHSU sign-corner vectors to guard the consolidated multiplier against signedness regressions.\"\n","additions":28,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r4s0.yaml","time":{"start":1778646570379,"end":1778646570381}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0ed17b1afccd9654016a03fe217a24819b914a68ebb4601721"}},"id":"prt_e1f98b31e001EkHYcxUeSUxDgu","sessionID":"ses_1e0680950ffeZxzoQM9CK3XRti","messageID":"msg_e1f98a8620019tUxWQNp1EK03f"}}
