{"type":"text","timestamp":1778652356643,"sessionID":"ses_1e00ff7aaffeWzLGKV4mWhOhuh","part":{"id":"prt_e1ff11b55001xsmB3pMgpgj5qn","messageID":"msg_e1ff10d8a001clGbneSg27Cusv","sessionID":"ses_1e00ff7aaffeWzLGKV4mWhOhuh","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single-file hypothesis that treats the existing BTB as worth keeping but trims redundant tag/target state and compare width in `if_stage.sv`, aiming for a front-end Fmax gain without changing prediction behavior.","time":{"start":1778652355413,"end":1778652356642},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_055241557c30fb4b016a0414c353f4819b980e5d60715b6aa7","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778652363725,"sessionID":"ses_1e00ff7aaffeWzLGKV4mWhOhuh","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_WMAGvPhttEkXRVZirtfB5AfW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r6s0\n+title: \"Trim BTB tag compare\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The current 16-entry direct-mapped BTB remains one of the few successful IPC improvements, but its IF-stage lookup still stores and compares the full 32-bit fetch PC even though the low two alignment bits and the index bits are redundant. Prior predictor-policy and capacity changes regressed by adding front-end logic, so the safer micro-opt path is to keep identical prediction behavior while reducing the lookup cone and state width.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the BTB's full btb_pc array with a compact tag containing only pc[31:BTB_INDEX_BITS+2], and store targets as word addresses plus two implicit zero low bits. The fetch hit check and update same-entry check then use a narrower tag compare, while the existing direct-mapped index, 2-bit counter policy, redirect priority, and EX-stage update semantics stay unchanged. This should slightly shorten the IF next-PC path and reduce LUT/FF pressure without changing CoreMark cycle count or any architectural state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace full-PC BTB tags with compact non-index PC tags and store aligned target word addresses, preserving the existing lookup/update behavior with less IF-stage compare and array width.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r6s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.clau