{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778654478880,"sessionID":"ses_1dfef2e2bffeNR1xJ9ZgdbqeaU","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Hs14gQFS5ldYc3ecJ4Cejfh1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful recent hypotheses for this core have been small local reductions\n+  in LUT depth, muxing, or state width that preserve the current pipeline behavior.\n+  The EX/MEM bundle still carries branch_taken and branch_target even though no\n+  downstream stage consumes them, and ctrl.is_lui is decoded and transported\n+  through every pipeline register even though LUI is already represented by\n+  alu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src. These dead bits add flops, fanout, and routing in\n+  the execute and decode cones without contributing to RVFI or architectural state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove unused pipeline/control payload: delete ctrl_t.is_lui, the decoder and\n+  ID-stage wiring that only feeds it, and the EX/MEM branch_taken and branch_target\n+  fields and assignments. Keep all existing branch resolution, redirect, BTB update,\n+  RVFI pc_wdata, trap, and register-write behavior unchanged. This should slightly\n+  reduce EX-stage register input fanout and inter-stage bundle width, improving Tang\n+  Nano 20K Fmax and LUT/FF pressure without changing CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove dead ctrl_t.is_lui and unused EX/MEM branch_taken and branch_target fields from the packed pipeline bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the is_lui output and assignments while preserving LUI decode via ALU_LUI, alu_src, and reg_write.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the dead decoded is_lui signal and ctrl_t assignment from the ID-stage decode path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop registering unused branch_taken and branch_target payload while leaving redirect, pc_next, and BPU update logic intact.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful recent hypotheses for this core have been small local reductions\n+  in LUT depth, muxing, or state width that preserve the current pipeline behavior.\n+  The EX/MEM bundle still carries branch_taken and branch_target even though no\n+  downstream stage consumes them, and ctrl.is_lui is decoded and transported\n+  through every pipeline register even though LUI is already represented by\n+  alu_op=ALU_LUI plus alu_src. These dead bits add flops, fanout, and routing in\n+  the execute and decode cones without contributing to RVFI or architectural state.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove unused pipeline/control payload: delete ctrl_t.is_lui, the decoder and\n+  ID-stage wiring that only feeds it, and the EX/MEM branch_taken and branch_target\n+  fields and assignments. Keep all existing branch resolution, redirect, BTB update,\n+  RVFI pc_wdata, trap, and register-write behavior unchanged. This should slightly\n+  reduce EX-stage register input fanout and inter-stage bundle width, improving Tang\n+  Nano 20K Fmax and LUT/FF pressure without changing CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove dead ctrl_t.is_lui and unused EX/MEM branch_taken and branch_target fields from the packed pipeline bundles.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Drop the is_lui output and assignments while preserving LUI decode via ALU_LUI, alu_src, and reg_write.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the dead decoded is_lui signal and ctrl_t assignment from the ID-stage decode path.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop registering unused branch_taken and branch_target payload while leaving redirect, pc_next, and BPU update logic intact.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r7s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r7s0\n+title: \"Prune dead pipeline payload\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The successful recent hypotheses for this core have been small local reductions\n+  in LUT depth, muxing, or state width that preserve the current pipeline 