{"type":"text","timestamp":1778656610156,"sessionID":"ses_1dfce6a9effe77WsWqR6kQ5gs1","part":{"id":"prt_e203203fb001A4UOHfQsLYDmZL","messageID":"msg_e2031dde0001BF5cY4xgTnfrhs","sessionID":"ses_1dfce6a9effe77WsWqR6kQ5gs1","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis for folding the redundant `mem_to_reg` control bit into `mem_read`, which trims one control bit across every pipeline register and removes associated decode/writeback mux control wiring without changing behavior.","time":{"start":1778656609275,"end":1778656610154},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_082b4db902feb4ff016a04256126b0819aba1ad684070c7b33","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778656619933,"sessionID":"ses_1dfce6a9effe77WsWqR6kQ5gs1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_78KySAX994kt84zKTIVwwXeA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r8s0\n+title: \"Fold load writeback select\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest recent wins for cores/bench have come from behavior-preserving\n+  datapath and payload reductions, especially pruning dead or duplicate control\n+  carried through the pipeline. The current ctrl_t still includes mem_to_reg,\n+  but in this RV32IM pipeline that bit is set exactly for loads and is therefore\n+  redundant with mem_read. Carrying both bits through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB\n+  adds decode fanout, register width, and writeback mux control pressure without\n+  improving CoreMark IPC or architectural precision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg and use ctrl.mem_read wherever the pipeline needs to\n+  select formatted load data instead of the ALU/JAL result. Decoder LOAD arms\n+  should set only mem_read, MEM-stage forwarding should choose load_data when\n+  mem_read is true, and WB should use mem_read as the writeback-data select.\n+  Misaligned loads already clear reg_write through the trap path, so the selected\n+  ignored data value is not architecturally visible. This should trim one hot\n+  control bit and its muxing across the full pipeline while preserving the NRET=1\n+  RVFI contract, load/store masks, traps, and CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field so the packed control payload is one bit narrower in every pipeline register.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop driving mem_to_reg in defaults and LOAD decode; mem_read remains the single load-result indicator.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the decoded mem_to_reg wire and assignment from the ID-stage control bundle construction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use ctrl.mem_read instead of ctrl.mem_to_reg for MEM-stage forwarding of formatted load data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use ctrl.mem_read as the writeback mux select between read_data and alu_result.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,34 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r8s0\n+title: \"Fold load writeback select\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  The strongest recent wins for cores/bench have come from behavior-preserving\n+  datapath and payload reductions, especially pruning dead or duplicate control\n+  carried through the pipeline. The current ctrl_t still includes mem_to_reg,\n+  but in this RV32IM pipeline that bit is set exactly for loads and is therefore\n+  redundant with mem_read. Carrying both bits through ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB\n+  adds decode fanout, register width, and writeback mux control pressure without\n+  improving CoreMark IPC or architectural precision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Remove ctrl_t.mem_to_reg and use ctrl.mem_read wherever the pipeline needs to\n+  select formatted load data instead of the ALU/JAL result. Decoder LOAD arms\n+  should set only mem_read, MEM-stage forwarding should choose load_data when\n+  mem_read is true, and WB should use mem_read as the writeback-data select.\n+  Misaligned loads already clear reg_write through the trap path, so the selected\n+  ignored data value is not architecturally visible. This should trim one hot\n+  control bit and its muxing across the full pipeline while preserving the NRET=1\n+  RVFI contract, load/store masks, traps, and CoreMark cycle count.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the redundant ctrl_t.mem_to_reg field so the packed control payload is one bit narrower in every pipeline register.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Stop driving mem_to_reg in defaults and LOAD decode; mem_read remains the single load-result indicator.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Remove the decoded mem_to_reg wire and assignment from the ID-stage control bundle construction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use ctrl.mem_read instead of ctrl.mem_to_reg for MEM-stage forwarding of formatted load data.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use ctrl.mem_read as the writeback mux select between read_data and alu_result.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r8s0.yaml\n