{"type":"text","timestamp":1778659966372,"sessionID":"ses_1df9bf666ffeI9g3Xz10pafGkf","part":{"id":"prt_e206536b90014WiwbE3Gee8EDB","messageID":"msg_e20645b97001OzzGr3rUvl0A5Z","sessionID":"ses_1df9bf666ffeI9g3Xz10pafGkf","type":"text","text":"The strongest unexplored micro-opt is another payload-pruning pass: remove duplicated register-address fields from pipeline bundles and derive them from the already-carried instruction word. This preserves the RVFI raw source-field requirement while trimming repeated 5-bit fields across ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB.","time":{"start":1778659964601,"end":1778659966369},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0a9878e5a898d088016a04327c7b64819baa2745c9056e723b","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778659997990,"sessionID":"ses_1df9bf666ffeI9g3Xz10pafGkf","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_9pvCwcR9yipcNY8pAUe5379u","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r9s0\n+title: \"Prune duplicate register fields\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent successful bench-core changes have been behavior-preserving reductions in\n+  datapath width, control fanout, and inter-stage payload. The pipeline currently\n+  carries rd, rs1_addr, and rs2_addr as explicit fields in multiple bundles even\n+  though the full instruction word is already carried to every later stage for\n+  RVFI. Those duplicated register-address flops and mux inputs add routing and\n+  fanout without improving IPC or architectural precision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Delete the duplicated rd/rs1_addr/rs2_addr fields from the packed pipeline\n+  payloads and derive register addresses from the carried instruction bits at\n+  each use site: forwarding compares, writeback address selection, and RVFI\n+  source/destination reporting. Keep raw instruction fields for RVFI rs1/rs2 so\n+  unused operands still report the same pre-write snapshots expected by cosim,\n+  and keep all reg_write/x0 gating unchanged. This should reduce flip-flops and\n+  routing pressure in the ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB cones without changing\n+  CoreMark cycle count, predictor behavior, traps, or the NRET=1 top-level port\n+  contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove duplicated rd, rs1_addr, and rs2_addr fields from ID/EX, EX/MEM, and MEM/WB bundles while keeping instr for RVFI and address derivation.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Stop latching explicit register-address payload fields; continue driving regfile read addresses from the raw instruction.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Derive source and destination register addresses from in.instr/out.instr when forwarding operands and building the EX/MEM payload.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate the instruction word only and remove explicit register-address assignments into MEM/WB.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use in.instr[11:7] as the writeback destination while preserving reg_write, valid, and x0 behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire forwarding and RVFI register-address fields from the corresponding pipeline instruction bits instead of removed payload fields.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-001-r9s0.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-001-r9s0\n+title: \"Prune duplicate register fields\"\n+category: micro_opt\n+motivation: |\n+  Recent successful bench-core changes have been behavior-preserving reductions in\n+  datapath width, control fanout, and inter-stage payload. The pipeline currently\n+  carries rd, rs1_addr, and rs2_addr as explicit fields in multiple bundles even\n+  though the full instruction word is already carried to every later stage for\n+  RVFI. Those duplicated register-address flops and mux inputs add routing and\n+  fanout without improving IPC or architectural precision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Delete the duplicated rd/