{"type":"text","timestamp":1778668474270,"sessionID":"ses_1df19dec9ffeSyITZKpXrxXYIM","part":{"id":"prt_e20e70b170018c1V7Rkqo3AyLm","messageID":"msg_e20e669e900126rCNQqYM1KqmL","sessionID":"ses_1df19dec9ffeSyITZKpXrxXYIM","type":"text","text":"The structural history rules out wider front-end buffering, ID control resolution, store posting, zero-bubble load-use, and MEM/WB boundary splits. The next best structural angle is to extend the latest successful EX datapath partitioning: keep common RV32I arithmetic off the monolithic RV32IM ALU/mul/div result cone while preserving single-cycle M behavior for correctness.","time":{"start":1778668473111,"end":1778668474269},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0cc079ca9dbaa304016a0453b900f8819b975858b1474990ed","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778668498836,"sessionID":"ses_1df19dec9ffeSyITZKpXrxXYIM","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_w4cYZXPI6RqjTd526rjM6PIa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: Split simple and M execute datapaths\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest successful structural change won by keeping CoreMark's hot load,\n+  store, and jump paths away from the monolithic RV32IM ALU result cone. The\n+  remaining arithmetic path still routes every ADD/SUB/logic/compare/shift\n+  through the same ALU module and output mux that also contains multiply,\n+  divide, and remainder hardware. CoreMark is dominated by RV32I integer work\n+  with occasional multiply at most, so isolating the rare M-extension cone from\n+  common integer operations should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing\n+  IPC, retirement width, or memory behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX into a two-lane arithmetic block: a lightweight simple_alu for\n+  RV32I ADD/SUB/logic/compare/shift/LUI operations and a separate m_alu path for\n+  MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU/DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU. Decode should carry a compact\n+  is_m_op bit so EX selects the M result only for funct7=0x01 operations; all\n+  other arithmetic writeback uses the simple lane, while LOAD/STORE and JAL/JALR\n+  continue using the dedicated paths added by the prior hypothesis. This keeps\n+  M-extension results single-cycle and RV32M-correct, including ALTOPS formal\n+  substitutions, but removes multiplier/divider result mux pressure and opcode\n+  fanout from the hot CoreMark RV32I execute path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact is_m_op control bit so EX can distinguish M-extension arithmetic from common RV32I arithmetic without re-decoding funct7.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Set is_m_op only for validated OP instructions with funct7=0x01 while preserving illegal-default decode and SYSTEM behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Split the current monolithic ALU into simple RV32I and M-extension result paths, keeping ALTOPS and exact RV32M corner cases intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate/select the simple and M arithmetic lanes so common RV32I operations bypass the multiplier/divider result cone while existing LSU, jump, forwarding, redirect, and RVFI semantics stay unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve ALU vectors to cover the split simple/M paths and guard RV32M bit-exact behavior after the datapath partition.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r12s1\n+title: Split simple and M execute datapaths\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest successful structural change won by keeping CoreMark's hot load,\n+  store, and jump paths away from the monolithic RV32IM ALU result cone. The\n+  remaining arithmetic path still routes every ADD/SUB/logic/compare/shift\n+  through the same ALU module and output mux that also contains multiply,\n+  divide, and remainder hardware. CoreMark is dominated by RV32I integer work\n+  with occasional multiply at most, so isolating the rare M-extension cone from\n+  common integer operations should improve Tang Nano 20K Fmax without changing\n+  IPC, retirement width, or memory behavior.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX into a two-lane arithmetic block: a lightweight simple_alu for\n+  RV32I ADD/SUB/logic/compare/shift/LUI operations and a separate m_alu path for\n+  MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU/DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU. Decode should carry a compact\n+  is_m_op bit so EX selects the M result only for funct7=0x01 operations; all\n+  other arithmetic writeback uses the simple lane, while LOAD/STORE and JAL/JALR\n+  continue using the dedicated paths added by the prior hypothesis. This keeps\n+  M-extension results single-cycle and RV32M-correct, including ALTOPS formal\n+  substitutions, but removes multiplier/divider result mux pressure and opcode\n+  fanout from the hot CoreMark RV32I execute path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact is_m_op control bit so EX can distinguish M-extension arithmetic from common RV32I arithmetic without re-decoding funct7.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Set is_m_op only for validated OP instructions with funct7=0x01 while preserving illegal-default decode and SYSTEM behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Split the current monolithic ALU into simple RV32I and M-extension result paths, keeping ALTOPS and exact RV32M corner cases intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate/select the simple and M arithmetic lanes so common RV32I operations bypass the multiplier/divider result cone while existing LSU, jump, forwarding, redirect, and RVFI semantics stay unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve ALU vectors to cover the split simple/M paths and guard RV32M bit-exact behavior after the datapath partition.\"\n\n","files":[{"fi