s keeps\n+  M-extension results single-cycle and RV32M-correct, including ALTOPS formal\n+  substitutions, but removes multiplier/divider result mux pressure and opcode\n+  fanout from the hot CoreMark RV32I execute path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a compact is_m_op control bit so EX can distinguish M-extension arithmetic from common RV32I arithmetic without re-decoding funct7.\"\n+  - file: rtl/decoder.sv\n+    description: \"Set is_m_op only for validated OP instructions with funct7=0x01 while preserving illegal-default decode and SYSTEM behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Split the current monolithic ALU into simple RV32I and M-extension result paths, keeping ALTOPS and exact RV32M corner cases intact.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate/select the simple and M arithmetic lanes so common RV32I operations bypass the multiplier/divider result cone while existing LSU, jump, forwarding, redirect, and RVFI semantics stay unchanged.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve ALU vectors to cover the split simple/M paths and guard RV32M bit-exact behavior after the datapath partition.\"\n","additions":36,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778668498832,"end":1778668498835}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cc079ca9dbaa304016a0453ba2dc0819b9cc03a9a584c4921"}},"id":"prt_e20e70f9e001doJmw2epcaSB96","sessionID":"ses_1df19dec9ffeSyITZKpXrxXYIM","messageID":"msg_e20e669e900126rCNQqYM1KqmL"}}
