ic block: a lightweight simple_alu for\n  RV32I ADD/SUB/logic/compare/shift/LUI operations and a separate m_alu path for\n  MUL/MULH/MULHU/MULHSU/DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU. Decode should carry a compact\n  is_m_op bit so EX selects the M result only for funct7=0x01 operations; all\n  other arithmetic writeback uses the simple lane, while LOAD/STORE and JAL/JALR\n  continue using the dedicated paths added by the prior hypothesis. This keeps\n  M-extension results single-cycle and RV32M-correct, including ALTOPS formal","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r12s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778668509665,"end":1778668509670}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0226244553840ad1016a0453dd1568819ba5b2920dccb15b27"}},"id":"prt_e20e79801001aCHgbpj3uCjjEa","sessionID":"ses_1df19dec9ffeSyITZKpXrxXYIM","messageID":"msg_e20e770990011B5jdTI9PEioBh"}}
