{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778670801114,"sessionID":"ses_1def73626ffeYKtoPSemtBHeh1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_NiF1yIOd66AEVKUnLkpKyrRD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Add fast addsub execute lane\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest successful structural change improved fitness by splitting common\n+  CoreMark LOAD/STORE and JAL/JALR result producers away from the monolithic\n+  RV32IM ALU. The remaining hot integer address-update and loop-counter work\n+  still routes ADD, ADDI, SUB, and AUIPC through the full ALU case tree and\n+  output mux that also contains shifts, compares, multiply, divide, and\n+  remainder. Prior broad execute-lane splits regressed when they added M-op\n+  control and duplicate routing, so the safer structural angle is a very narrow\n+  fast lane for the most common add/sub class only.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX so ADD/ADDI/SUB/AUIPC arithmetic has a dedicated fast adder\n+  lane beside the existing LSU address adder and JAL pc+4 path. For these\n+  opcodes, drive the EX/MEM result from the small add/sub lane and gate the\n+  full ALU inputs to zero; keep the existing ALU for logic, shifts, compares,\n+  LUI, and all RV32M operations. This should shorten CoreMark's frequent\n+  integer update writeback path and reduce full-ALU result mux pressure without\n+  changing pipeline depth, load-use interlocks, forwarding, traps, RVFI fields,\n+  or the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated ADD/ADDI/SUB/AUIPC fast result lane, select it before the full ALU for those arithmetic ops, and gate full-ALU operands when the fast lane is used.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally remove or leave unreachable ADD/SUB pressure after EX gating, while preserving logic, shift, compare, LUI, RV32M, and ALTOPS behavior exactly.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Add fast addsub execute lane\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest successful structural change improved fitness by splitting common\n+  CoreMark LOAD/STORE and JAL/JALR result producers away from the monolithic\n+  RV32IM ALU. The remaining hot integer address-update and loop-counter work\n+  still routes ADD, ADDI, SUB, and AUIPC through the full ALU case tree and\n+  output mux that also contains shifts, compares, multiply, divide, and\n+  remainder. Prior broad execute-lane splits regressed when they added M-op\n+  control and duplicate routing, so the safer structural angle is a very narrow\n+  fast lane for the most common add/sub class only.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX so ADD/ADDI/SUB/AUIPC arithmetic has a dedicated fast adder\n+  lane beside the existing LSU address adder and JAL pc+4 path. For these\n+  opcodes, drive the EX/MEM result from the small add/sub lane and gate the\n+  full ALU inputs to zero; keep the existing ALU for logic, shifts, compares,\n+  LUI, and all RV32M operations. This should shorten CoreMark's frequent\n+  integer update writeback path and reduce full-ALU result mux pressure without\n+  changing pipeline depth, load-use interlocks, forwarding, traps, RVFI fields,\n+  or the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated ADD/ADDI/SUB/AUIPC fast result lane, select it before the full ALU for those arithmetic ops, and gate full-ALU operands when the fast lane is used.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally remove or leave unreachable ADD/SUB pressure after EX gating, while preserving logic, shift, compare, LUI, RV32M, and ALTOPS behavior exactly.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r13s1\n+title: \"Add fast addsub execute lane\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The latest successful structural change improved fitness by splitting common\n+  CoreMark LOAD/STORE and JAL/JALR result producers away from the monolithic\n+  RV32IM ALU. The remaining hot integer address-update and loop-counter work\n+  still routes ADD, ADDI, SUB, and AUIPC through the full ALU case tree and\n+  output mux that also contains shifts, compares, multiply, divide, and\n+  remainder. Prior broad execute-lane splits regressed when they added M-op\n+  control and duplicate routing, so the safer structural angle is a very narrow\n+  fast lane for the most common add/sub class only.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure EX so ADD/ADDI/SUB/AUIPC arithmetic has a dedicated fast adder\n+  lane beside the existing LSU address adder and JAL pc+4 path. For these\n+  opcodes, drive the EX/MEM result from the small add/sub lane and gate the\n+  full ALU inputs to zero; keep the existing ALU for logic, shifts, compares,\n+  LUI, and all RV32M operations. This should shorten CoreMark's frequent\n+  integer update writeback path and reduce full-ALU result mux pressure without\n+  changing pipeline depth, load-use interlocks, forwarding, traps, RVFI fields,\n+  or the NRET=1 top-level contract.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a dedicated ADD/ADDI/SUB/AUIPC fast result lane, select it before the full ALU for those arithmetic ops, and gate full-ALU operands when the fast lane is used.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Optionally remove or leave unreachable ADD/SUB pressure after EX gating, while preserving logic, shift, compare, LUI, RV32M, and ALTOPS behavior exactly.\"\n","additions":29,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r13s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778670801107,"end":1778670801113}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0629e3168ca67db7016a045cbdfe50819babe931f9151d99cc"}},"id":"prt_e210a4681001I9HT8pZTlNOs9V","sessionID":"ses_1def73626ffeYKtoPSemtBHeh1","messageID":"msg_e210a3ee9001ws7Tziq3ds3Cwy"}}
