{"type":"text","timestamp":1778673185529,"sessionID":"ses_1ded29506ffe3z1sCIcAbKjCr0","part":{"id":"prt_e212ef282001eWXpeFLLtfigOp","messageID":"msg_e212e2102001zdgAiTWveqx3JZ","sessionID":"ses_1ded29506ffe3z1sCIcAbKjCr0","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a structural hypothesis focused on narrowing post-EX control payloads, extending the earlier successful payload-pruning pattern without adding buffers, predictors, or new stall policy.","time":{"start":1778673185410,"end":1778673185528},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d40a38e2fec94b0016a0466214964819b9a85258a4ef1e881","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778673208724,"sessionID":"ses_1ded29506ffe3z1sCIcAbKjCr0","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_kmo7HEL0Uk9IpVuufJusZUjC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"Narrow post-EX control payload\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline still carries the full decoded ctrl_t through EX/MEM and\n+  MEM/WB even though most of those bits are dead after execute. MEM only needs\n+  memory access shape, writeback select, reg_write, and trap state, while WB and\n+  RVFI only need reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal. Prior successful work\n+  showed that pruning real inter-stage payload and fanout can improve Tang Nano\n+  20K fitness, while broader structural changes that add buffering or new stall\n+  control tend to regress.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the full ctrl_t fields in ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t with narrower\n+  stage-specific packed control structs. EX should translate the decoded ctrl_t\n+  into a mem-stage control record containing only mem_read, mem_write,\n+  mem_width, mem_sext, reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal. MEM should then\n+  translate that into a writeback/retirement control record containing only\n+  reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal. This preserves all existing pipeline\n+  timing, load-use interlocks, dmem-stall hold behavior, RVFI trap reporting,\n+  and the NRET=1 top-level port contract, but reduces flop count, mux inputs,\n+  and routing fanout on the EX/MEM and MEM/WB boundaries.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add narrow post-EX and writeback control structs and use them in ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t instead of carrying full ctrl_t past execute.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pack only the MEM-stage control bits into EX/MEM while preserving existing misalignment trap and reg_write suppression behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the narrow MEM control record, generate memory masks/load data as today, and emit only the WB/RVFI control bits into MEM/WB.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the narrow writeback control record for regfile write enable and load-vs-ALU writeback selection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Update hazard, forwarding, RVFI, and writeback wiring to reference the narrowed post-EX control fields without changing port shape or retirement order.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r14s1\n+title: \"Narrow post-EX control payload\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current pipeline still carries the full decoded ctrl_t through EX/MEM and\n+  MEM/WB even though most of those bits are dead after execute. MEM only needs\n+  memory access shape, writeback select, reg_write, and trap state, while WB and\n+  RVFI only need reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal. Prior successful work\n+  showed that pruning real inter-stage payload and fanout can improve Tang Nano\n+  20K fitness, while broader structural changes that add buffering or new stall\n+  control tend to regress.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the full ctrl_t fields in ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t with narrower\n+  stage-specific packed control structs. EX should translate the decoded ctrl_t\n+  into a mem-stage control record containing only mem_read, mem_write,\n+  mem_width, mem_sext, reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal. MEM should then\n+  translate that into a writeback/retirement control record containing only\n+  reg_write, mem_to_reg, and is_illegal. This preserves all existing pipeline\n+  timing, load-use interlocks, dmem-stall hold behavior, RVFI trap reporting,\n+  and the NRET=1 top-level port contract, but reduces flop count, mux inputs,\n+  and routing fanout on the EX/MEM and MEM/WB boundaries.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add narrow post-EX and writeback control structs and use them in ex_mem_t and mem_wb_t instead of carrying full ctrl_t past execute.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pack only the MEM-stage control bits into EX/MEM while preserving existing misalignment trap and reg_write suppression behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the narrow MEM control record, generate memory masks/load data as today, and emit only the WB/RVFI control bits into MEM/WB.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the narrow writeback control record for regfile write enable and load-vs-ALU writeback selection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Update hazard, forwarding, RVFI, and writeback wiring to reference the narrowed post-EX control fields without changing port shape or retirement order.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/core