of carrying full ctrl_t past execute.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pack only the MEM-stage control bits into EX/MEM while preserving existing misalignment trap and reg_write suppression behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Consume the narrow MEM control record, generate memory masks/load data as today, and emit only the WB/RVFI control bits into MEM/WB.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the narrow writeback control record for regfile write enable and load-vs-ALU writeback selection.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Update hazard, forwarding, RVFI, and writeback wiring to reference the narrowed post-EX control fields without changing port shape or retirement order.\"\n","additions":35,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r14s1.yaml","time":{"start":1778673208717,"end":1778673208722}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d40a38e2fec94b0016a0466216d50819bbe4f872c322d2a11"}},"id":"prt_e212ef2f9001YROpU3kjaW95ag","sessionID":"ses_1ded29506ffe3z1sCIcAbKjCr0","messageID":"msg_e212e2102001zdgAiTWveqx3JZ"}}
