{"type":"text","timestamp":1778675432682,"sessionID":"ses_1deb04b84ffetArzI5J9WVDGov","part":{"id":"prt_e215135d6001Q142lw09ydjptz","messageID":"msg_e214ffdcc002L643TNIOyNr2Ym","sessionID":"ses_1deb04b84ffetArzI5J9WVDGov","type":"text","text":"The structural history strongly discourages new buffering, early branch resolution, store posting, same-cycle load-use, or broader lane splits. The most promising remaining structural angle is narrower datapath isolation: split the EX/MEM arithmetic writeback result from the LSU address bus so hot ALU results no longer fan out through MEM address/mask/load-format logic.","time":{"start":1778675430870,"end":1778675432680},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_02f72fd0b0edecf8016a046ee6be2081989d02375c3c31eace","phase":"commentary"}}}}
