{"type":"text","timestamp":1778642840811,"sessionID":"ses_1e0a1111bffeeHsqnmeRCd93cW","part":{"id":"prt_e1f5fec76001esxia4xGi6fVqh","messageID":"msg_e1f5f1694001MKyeFC6AVjztmQ","sessionID":"ses_1e0a1111bffeeHsqnmeRCd93cW","type":"text","text":"Prior structural attempts point away from more front-end buffering or ID control resolution because they increased front-end mux/compare depth. The most promising structural slot is to remove the unused one-cycle divide/remainder path from EX’s critical path while keeping common integer and multiply throughput intact.","time":{"start":1778642840694,"end":1778642840810},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_06d7dc03194ca0e3016a03ef989a20819996da660f8be67c1a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
