{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778642862278,"sessionID":"ses_1e0a1111bffeeHsqnmeRCd93cW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_yAf8pEmw5Kye2puUtYLAVetu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Move div/rem off EX critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU keeps RV32M division and remainder as single-cycle\n+  combinational operations in the EX stage. CoreMark's timed path is dominated\n+  by loads, branches, integer ALU work, and multiplication, while DIV/REM are\n+  rare or absent. Keeping a full divider on every EX-cycle timing path likely\n+  costs Fmax and LUTs without improving CoreMark iterations per cycle.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the M-extension structure so common ALU operations and MUL/MULH stay on\n+  the existing one-cycle EX path, but DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU are handled by a small\n+  multi-cycle divider sidecar that stalls the pipeline only when one of those\n+  opcodes reaches EX. This should remove the long combinational divide/remainder\n+  network from the EX/MEM register timing path and recover FPGA Fmax, while\n+  preserving CoreMark IPC because the benchmark should not depend on frequent\n+  divisions. The sidecar must keep RV32M corner-case results exact, keep ALTOPS\n+  behavior for fast formal runs, and retire the original instruction only after\n+  the computed result is available.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact control metadata, if needed, to identify DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as multi-cycle EX operations without changing the NRET=1 RVFI bundle shape.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/REM from the one-cycle combinational ALU path while keeping normal ALU, MUL-family, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS results consistent.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate or integrate a small multi-cycle divider/remainder unit, hold the EX instruction until completion, and drive the final result into EX/MEM exactly once.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX multi-cycle stall input that freezes IF/ID and ID/EX without creating duplicate retirements, with redirect and dmem-stall priority preserved.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider-busy stall between EX and the hazard logic while preserving the existing top-level IO and single-channel RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve RV32M division and remainder vectors so the sidecar's divide-by-zero and signed-overflow corner cases remain covered.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r3s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r3s1\n+title: \"Move div/rem off EX critical path\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current ALU keeps RV32M division and remainder as single-cycle\n+  combinational operations in the EX stage. CoreMark's timed path is dominated\n+  by loads, branches, integer ALU work, and multiplication, while DIV/REM are\n+  rare or absent. Keeping a full divider on every EX-cycle timing path likely\n+  costs Fmax and LUTs without improving CoreMark iterations per cycle.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Split the M-extension structure so common ALU operations and MUL/MULH stay on\n+  the existing one-cycle EX path, but DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU are handled by a small\n+  multi-cycle divider sidecar that stalls the pipeline only when one of those\n+  opcodes reaches EX. This should remove the long combinational divide/remainder\n+  network from the EX/MEM register timing path and recover FPGA Fmax, while\n+  preserving CoreMark IPC because the benchmark should not depend on frequent\n+  divisions. The sidecar must keep RV32M corner-case results exact, keep ALTOPS\n+  behavior for fast formal runs, and retire the original instruction only after\n+  the computed result is available.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add compact control metadata, if needed, to identify DIV/DIVU/REM/REMU as multi-cycle EX operations without changing the NRET=1 RVFI bundle shape.\"\n+  - file: rtl/alu.sv\n+    description: \"Remove real DIV/REM from the one-cycle combinational ALU path while keeping normal ALU, MUL-family, and RISCV_FORMAL_ALTOPS results consistent.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Instantiate or integrate a small multi-cycle divider/remainder unit, hold the EX instruction until completion, and drive the final result into EX/MEM exactly once.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Add an EX multi-cycle stall input that freezes IF/ID and ID/EX without creating duplicate retirements, with redirect and dmem-stall priority preserved.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the divider-busy stall between EX and the hazard logic while preserving the existing top-level IO and single-channel RVFI contract.\"\n+  - file: test/test_alu.py\n+    description: \"Extend or preserve RV32M division and remainder vectors so the sidecar's divide-by-zero and signed-overflow corner cases remain covered.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.cla