{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1778649091909,"sessionID":"ses_1e040dbb3ffeP70xMfaVwwgP00","part":{"id":"prt_e1fbf4f44001iWjThVsqTy8gEz","messageID":"msg_e1fbf4a6e002GHLUfVga50nN7T","sessionID":"ses_1e040dbb3ffeP70xMfaVwwgP00","snapshot":"0bd3fe688b9f526104a662838fa6f369f2ee5d41","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1778649120910,"sessionID":"ses_1e040dbb3ffeP70xMfaVwwgP00","part":{"id":"prt_e1fbfbfd6001nBDIrz6vF91TeF","messageID":"msg_e1fbf4a6e002GHLUfVga50nN7T","sessionID":"ses_1e040dbb3ffeP70xMfaVwwgP00","type":"text","text":"The prior structural attempts clustered around fetch buffering, early control resolution, DIV sidecar, and posted stores; all either regressed or had marginal gains because they added control muxing to hot paths. I’m going to propose a narrower retiming structural change that targets the current combined fetch/decode/register-file path without adding predictors or memory ordering machinery.","time":{"start":1778649120726,"end":1778649120909},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0096abe3c2060cea016a040820a3cc8198bcd177857df900c4","phase":"commentary"}}}}
