{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778649178748,"sessionID":"ses_1e040dbb3ffeP70xMfaVwwgP00","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_VvATmRMncScQwHEe8Fw93T8o","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r5s1\n+title: \"Split execute and RVFI forwarding\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current forwarding network uses the MEM-stage formatted writeback value for\n+  both execute operands and RVFI source snapshots. That keeps the dmem read-data\n+  formatting path connected to the EX operand muxes even though true load-use\n+  consumers are already stalled until the load reaches MEM/WB. Prior wins show\n+  that the dmem-to-forwarding path matters, while prior broken source-use work\n+  shows RVFI raw source snapshots must still be preserved.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure forwarding into two planes: an execute plane that forwards only\n+  ALU/JAL results from EX/MEM and WB data from MEM/WB, and an RVFI snapshot\n+  plane that can still forward the formatted MEM-stage load value for raw rs1\n+  and rs2 reporting. EX should use the execute plane for ALU operands, branch\n+  compares, JALR targets, and store write data; the separately computed RVFI\n+  operands should be carried in ex_mem_t.rs1_val/rs2_val exactly as today. This\n+  removes the load-format/dmem_rdata cone from common execute timing without\n+  changing retirement width, load-use interlocks, memory ordering, or RVFI\n+  source-field semantics.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Produce separate execute-forwarding and RVFI-source-forwarding selects, suppressing EX/MEM load selection only on the execute plane.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the execute forwarding plane for real operands and a separate RVFI forwarding plane for rs1_val/rs2_val captured into EX/MEM.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire distinct EX/MEM ALU-result and MEM-stage formatted-result paths into the split forwarding network and EX stage.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r5s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r5s1\n+title: \"Split execute and RVFI forwarding\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current forwarding network uses the MEM-stage formatted writeback value for\n+  both execute operands and RVFI source snapshots. That keeps the dmem read-data\n+  formatting path connected to the EX operand muxes even though true load-use\n+  consumers are already stalled until the load reaches MEM/WB. Prior wins show\n+  that the dmem-to-forwarding path matters, while prior broken source-use work\n+  shows RVFI raw source snapshots must still be preserved.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Restructure forwarding into two planes: an execute plane that forwards only\n+  ALU/JAL results from EX/MEM and WB data from MEM/WB, and an RVFI snapshot\n+  plane that can still forward the formatted MEM-stage load value for raw rs1\n+  and rs2 reporting. EX should use the execute plane for ALU operands, branch\n+  compares, JALR targets, and store write data; the separately computed RVFI\n+  operands should be carried in ex_mem_t.rs1_val/rs2_val exactly as today. This\n+  removes the load-format/dmem_rdata cone 