{"type":"text","timestamp":1778652331659,"sessionID":"ses_1e00ff80dffes22j7NX1ZsgBh6","part":{"id":"prt_e1ff0bd54001ahuiBzCzAbHhxJ","messageID":"msg_e1ff0a80e002jK7ib4bxYjUk0d","sessionID":"ses_1e00ff80dffes22j7NX1ZsgBh6","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis file now, scoped only to `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/` and referencing editable RTL files with the required short paths.","time":{"start":1778652331348,"end":1778652331657},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_038f8d3739972d05016a0414ab433881989e50b198e93e4184","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778652342002,"sessionID":"ses_1e00ff80dffes22j7NX1ZsgBh6","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_YFkyE8GvfcKYQADQdY90oIIs","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r6s1\n+title: \"Register IF/ID boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The bench core currently has a PC register in IF, but the IF/ID payload is\n+  combinational: imem data, raw instruction fields, decoder outputs, immediate\n+  generation, and regfile read addresses all feed the ID/EX register in one\n+  cycle. Prior structural attempts that added predictors, buffers, or early\n+  control logic regressed because they lengthened IF-side muxing or broad\n+  pipeline control. A narrower structural retiming can attack the same frontend\n+  timing pressure without adding a larger predictor or side buffer.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert IF/ID into a true registered pipeline boundary that captures pc,\n+  predicted pc, instruction, and valid when imem is ready, holds across ID or\n+  dmem stalls, and flushes on redirects. This cuts the imem-data-to-decode and\n+  imem-data-to-regfile-address path out of the ID/EX setup cone, and the single\n+  registered entry can also let ID consume one already-fetched instruction when\n+  the next imem access stalls. The cost is one extra frontend stage and a larger\n+  redirect bubble on unpredicted control flow, but CoreMark's hot loop branches\n+  are already helped by the existing BTB, so the expected net gain is higher\n+  Fmax plus modest iStall tolerance with much less control complexity than the\n+  earlier skid-buffer attempt.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Move pc/instr/pred_pc/valid into an IF/ID register with redirect flush, ID hold, and imem-ready capture semantics while preserving BTB redirect priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Separate fetch-stage stall/hold decisions from decode bubbles so imem backpressure does not force a NOP when a registered IF/ID instruction is available.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/ID hold and flush controls between hazard, IF, and ID without changing the NRET=1 top-level RVFI or memory port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r6s1\n+title: \"Register IF/ID boundary\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The bench core currently has a PC register in IF, but the IF/ID payload is\n+  combinational: imem data, raw instruction fields, decoder outputs, immediate\n+  generation, and regfile read addresses all feed the ID/EX register in one\n+  cycle. Prior structural attempts that added predictors, buffers, or early\n+  control logic regressed because they lengthened IF-side muxing or broad\n+  pipeline control. A narrower structural retiming can attack the same frontend\n+  timing pressure without adding a larger predictor or side buffer.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Convert IF/ID into a true registered pipeline boundary that captures pc,\n+  predicted pc, instruction, and valid when imem is ready, holds across ID or\n+  dmem stalls, and flushes on redirects. This cuts the imem-data-to-decode and\n+  imem-data-to-regfile-address path out of the ID/EX setup cone, and the single\n+  registered entry can also let ID consume one already-fetched instruction when\n+  the next imem access stalls. The cost is one extra frontend stage and a larger\n+  redirect bubble on unpredicted control flow, but CoreMark's hot loop branches\n+  are already helped by the existing BTB, so the expected net gain is higher\n+  Fmax plus modest iStall tolerance with much less control complexity than the\n+  earlier skid-buffer attempt.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 3\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Move pc/instr/pred_pc/valid into an IF/ID register with redirect flush, ID hold, and imem-ready capture semantics while preserving BTB redirect priority.\"\n+  - file: rtl/hazard_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Separate fetch-stage stall/hold decisions from decode bubbles so imem backpressure does not force a NOP when a registered IF/ID instruction is available.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the revised IF/ID hold and flush controls between hazard, IF, and ID without changing the NRET=1 top-level RVFI or memory port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r6s1.yaml\n@