{"type":"text","timestamp":1778656665390,"sessionID":"ses_1dfce6a2effeX23v3w0HOigY2k","part":{"id":"prt_e2032df2b002QBLzAciBEespbd","messageID":"msg_e2032ca84001TfARL1BvQC12Nz","sessionID":"ses_1dfce6a2effeX23v3w0HOigY2k","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis YAML now under `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/` with only `rtl/...` change paths.","time":{"start":1778656665387,"end":1778656665389},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0ad8de202183af64016a04259931ac8198a5987854a0c0ca3a","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778656676033,"sessionID":"ses_1dfce6a2effeX23v3w0HOigY2k","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_AsBb390kVz30aEKgPweixwFK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Retire directly from MEM\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current bench core still carries a full MEM/WB register and a separate\n+  combinational WB stage even though MEM already computes the final writeback\n+  value, formatted load data, memory masks, and RVFI memory fields. Recent wins\n+  came from pruning dead pipeline payload and shortening local datapath cones,\n+  while prior structural regressions came from adding front-end buffers,\n+  earlier branch logic, store buffers, or same-cycle dmem-to-EX pressure. A\n+  MEM-stage retirement boundary attacks pipeline structure and routing pressure\n+  without adding predictor state or changing the NRET=1 contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Collapse writeback/retirement into the MEM stage: compute the final rd write\n+  data from the current EX/MEM payload, write the regfile from that MEM-stage\n+  commit value, and drive RVFI channel 0 from the same commit record when the\n+  memory operation is actually accepted. Keep the existing one-cycle load-use\n+  interlock, but remove the broad MEM/WB payload and replace MEM/WB forwarding\n+  with MEM-stage forwarding plus the regfile's same-cycle write-first bypass\n+  for instructions two cycles behind a producer. This should reduce flop count,\n+  forwarding mux fan-in, and routing fanout on every instruction while keeping\n+  CoreMark's steady-state single-retire IPC and bus-ordering semantics intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Move the retirement/writeback boundary from MEM/WB to MEM-stage commit signals, delete the wb_stage instance, and keep rvfi_order tied to accepted MEM commits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose final commit fields, formatted load data, masks, and regfile writeback data directly from the current EX/MEM payload while gating valid during dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reduce forwarding to the current MEM-stage producer plus regfile write-first behavior, eliminating the MEM/WB producer input.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove or shrink the MEM/WB bundle after RVFI commit fields are generated directly at MEM-stage retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the now-redundant standalone writeback mux or leave it unused if the implementation keeps the file for build ordering simplicity.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-002-r8s1.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,36 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-002-r8s1\n+title: \"Retire directly from MEM\"\n+category: structural\n+motivation: |\n+  The current bench core still carries a full MEM/WB register and a separate\n+  combinational WB stage even though MEM already computes the final writeback\n+  value, formatted load data, memory masks, and RVFI memory fields. Recent wins\n+  came from pruning dead pipeline payload and shortening local datapath cones,\n+  while prior structural regressions came from adding front-end buffers,\n+  earlier branch logic, store buffers, or same-cycle dmem-to-EX pressure. A\n+  MEM-stage retirement boundary attacks pipeline structure and routing pressure\n+  without adding predictor state or changing the NRET=1 contract.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Collapse writeback/retirement into the MEM stage: compute the final rd write\n+  data from the current EX/MEM payload, write the regfile from that MEM-stage\n+  commit value, and drive RVFI channel 0 from the same commit record when the\n+  memory operation is actually accepted. Keep the existing one-cycle load-use\n+  interlock, but remove the broad MEM/WB payload and replace MEM/WB forwarding\n+  with MEM-stage forwarding plus the regfile's same-cycle write-first bypass\n+  for instructions two cycles behind a producer. This should reduce flop count,\n+  forwarding mux fan-in, and routing fanout on every instruction while keeping\n+  CoreMark's steady-state single-retire IPC and bus-ordering semantics intact.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 4\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Move the retirement/writeback boundary from MEM/WB to MEM-stage commit signals, delete the wb_stage instance, and keep rvfi_order tied to accepted MEM commits.\"\n+  - file: rtl/mem_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Expose final commit fields, formatted load data, masks, and regfile writeback data directly from the current EX/MEM payload while gating valid during dmem stalls.\"\n+  - file: rtl/forward_unit.sv\n+    description: \"Reduce forwarding to the current MEM-stage producer plus regfile write-first behavior, eliminating the MEM/WB producer input.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Remove or shrink the MEM/WB bundle after RVFI commit fields are generated directly at MEM-stage retirement.\"\n+  - file: rtl/wb_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Delete the now-redundant standalone writeback mux or leave it unused if the implementation keeps the file for build ordering simplicity.\"