{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778668503644,"sessionID":"ses_1df19dddcffelS3CeTtte84ugY","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_q7XTEjjMCPUYbaZTTEg9tK5D","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Gate prediction validation compare\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has consistently helped this core. Recent predictor\n+  attempts regressed when they added table capacity, IF instruction decode,\n+  update filtering, weaker hysteresis, delayed training, or victim/RAS state.\n+  A safer remaining predictor angle is to keep the same predictions while\n+  reducing the cost of validating those predictions in EX.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-bit predicted-taken flag to the IF/ID and ID/EX predictor metadata.\n+  IF sets it from the BTB hit and counter MSB, while still carrying the existing\n+  predicted next PC for taken-target validation. EX then only compares against\n+  the carried predicted target when the fetched instruction was predicted taken;\n+  not-predicted-taken control flow is validated against pc+4, and non-control\n+  instructions do not need the predicted-PC compare at all. This preserves the\n+  current BTB lookup, update policy, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 RVFI behavior,\n+  but should trim fanout and LUT depth from the common EX redirect path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a predicted-taken bit to the IF/ID and ID/EX predictor metadata while keeping the existing predicted target field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive the predicted-taken bit from the compact BTB hit/counter decision alongside the current predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the predicted-taken bit through ID/EX with the existing fetch PC and predicted next-PC metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the predicted-taken bit to gate prediction validation so ordinary and not-predicted-taken instructions avoid the full predicted-target compare.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Gate prediction validation compare\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has consistently helped this core. Recent predictor\n+  attempts regressed when they added table capacity, IF instruction decode,\n+  update filtering, weaker hysteresis, delayed training, or victim/RAS state.\n+  A safer remaining predictor angle is to keep the same predictions while\n+  reducing the cost of validating those predictions in EX.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-bit predicted-taken flag to the IF/ID and ID/EX predictor metadata.\n+  IF sets it from the BTB hit and counter MSB, while still carrying the existing\n+  predicted next PC for taken-target validation. EX then only compares against\n+  the carried predicted target when the fetched instruction was predicted taken;\n+  not-predicted-taken control flow is validated against pc+4, and non-control\n+  instructions do not need the predicted-PC compare at all. This preserves the\n+  current BTB lookup, update policy, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 RVFI behavior,\n+  but should trim fanout and LUT depth from the common EX redirect path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a predicted-taken bit to the IF/ID and ID/EX predictor metadata while keeping the existing predicted target field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive the predicted-taken bit from the compact BTB hit/counter decision alongside the current predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the predicted-taken bit through ID/EX with the existing fetch PC and predicted next-PC metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the predicted-taken bit to gate prediction validation so ordinary and not-predicted-taken instructions avoid the full predicted-target compare.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r12s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,31 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r12s2\n+title: \"Gate prediction validation compare\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has consistently helped this core. Recent predictor\n+  attempts regressed when they added table capacity, IF instruction decode,\n+  update filtering, weaker hysteresis, delayed training, or victim/RAS state.\n+  A safer remaining predictor angle is to keep the same predictions while\n+  reducing the cost of validating those predictions in EX.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a one-bit predicted-taken flag to the IF/ID and ID/EX predictor metadata.\n+  IF sets it from the BTB hit and counter MSB, while still carrying the existing\n+  predicted next PC for taken-target validation. EX then only compares against\n+  the carried predicted target when the fetched instruction was predicted taken;\n+  not-predicted-taken control flow is validated against pc+4, and non-control\n+  instructions do not need the predicted-PC compare at all. This preserves the\n+  current BTB lookup, update policy, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 RVFI behavior,\n+  but should trim fanout and LUT depth from the common EX redirect path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Add a predicted-taken bit to the IF/ID and ID/EX predictor metadata while keeping the existing predicted target field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Drive the predicted-taken bit from the compact BTB hit/counter decision alongside the current predicted next PC.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Pipeline the predicted-taken bit through ID/EX with the existing fetch PC and predicted next-PC metadata.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Use the predicted-taken bit to gate prediction validation so ordinary and not-predicted-taken instructions avoid the full predicted-target compare.\"\n","additions":31,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20