{"type":"text","timestamp":1778670740705,"sessionID":"ses_1def735c0ffe7cKiOb0Czje8hi","part":{"id":"prt_e21099d04001NJtlsxSkinkypf","messageID":"msg_e2109924c001iiRGsW5gJlv3rh","sessionID":"ses_1def735c0ffe7cKiOb0Czje8hi","type":"text","text":"Writing the hypothesis now as a small `if_stage.sv`/`ex_stage.sv` predictor change proposal, with no edits outside `cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/`.","time":{"start":1778670738692,"end":1778670740703},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0afa60caee89cd68016a045c9299c081998c15360301381c2d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778670760437,"sessionID":"ses_1def735c0ffe7cKiOb0Czje8hi","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_Lt3tSiqtopE6dqiGAda3OS4g","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Separate jump predictor state\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current compact 16-entry PC-only BTB with two-bit counters is still the\n+  only predictor structure that has produced a durable CoreMark win. Recent\n+  predictor attempts regressed when they changed table capacity, added\n+  instruction-dependent fetch logic, filtered conditional feedback, delayed\n+  updates, or added victim/RAS state. A safer remaining angle is to keep the\n+  proven lookup geometry but avoid spending conditional-branch hysteresis logic\n+  on unconditional jumps, which are always taken once their target is known.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a per-BTB-entry unconditional-jump marker set by EX for JAL/JALR updates.\n+  Fetch should predict a valid tag hit when either the entry is marked\n+  unconditional or the existing two-bit conditional counter is taken; conditional\n+  branches continue to use the same 2-bit counter policy and target storage.\n+  The update path should write jump entries as always-taken target entries and\n+  skip counter increment/decrement work for them, while branch entries keep the\n+  current weak allocation and saturating training. This preserves the 16-entry\n+  PC-only table, compact tags, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 contract, but may\n+  trim predictor update pressure and reduce alias damage between calls/jumps and\n+  conditional loop branches without adding IF-side instruction predecode.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a per-entry unconditional marker to the existing 16-entry BTB and use it with the current counter MSB for PC-only prediction, while preserving tag, target, reset, and redirect behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Classify BPU updates as unconditional for JAL/JALR versus conditional branches so IF can skip counter training for always-taken jump entries.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the new unconditional-update bit from EX to IF without changing the single-channel RVFI or memory port contract.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,32 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r13s2\n+title: \"Separate jump predictor state\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current compact 16-entry PC-only BTB with two-bit counters is still the\n+  only predictor structure that has produced a durable CoreMark win. Recent\n+  predictor attempts regressed when they changed table capacity, added\n+  instruction-dependent fetch logic, filtered conditional feedback, delayed\n+  updates, or added victim/RAS state. A safer remaining angle is to keep the\n+  proven lookup geometry but avoid spending conditional-branch hysteresis logic\n+  on unconditional jumps, which are always taken once their target is known.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a per-BTB-entry unconditional-jump marker set by EX for JAL/JALR updates.\n+  Fetch should predict a valid tag hit when either the entry is marked\n+  unconditional or the existing two-bit conditional counter is taken; conditional\n+  branches continue to use the same 2-bit counter policy and target storage.\n+  The update path should write jump entries as always-taken target entries and\n+  skip counter increment/decrement work for them, while branch entries keep the\n+  current weak allocation and saturating training. This preserves the 16-entry\n+  PC-only table, compact tags, redirect recovery, and NRET=1 contract, but may\n+  trim predictor update pressure and reduce alias damage between calls/jumps and\n+  conditional loop branches without adding IF-side instruction predecode.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Add a per-entry unconditional marker to the existing 16-entry BTB and use it with the current counter MSB for PC-only prediction, while preserving tag, target, reset, and redirect behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Classify BPU updates as unconditional for JAL/JALR versus conditional branches so IF can skip counter training for always-taken jump entries.\"\n+  - file: rtl/core.sv\n+    description: \"Wire the new unconditional-update bit from EX to IF without changing the single-channel RVFI or memory port contract.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r13s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tou