{"type":"text","timestamp":1778675433549,"sessionID":"ses_1deb04b20ffeyLsV1q0iKnZoLD","part":{"id":"prt_e21513b11001cwzu72rZaFniI6","messageID":"msg_e215028a600156pRUY5FshDNRR","sessionID":"ses_1deb04b20ffeyLsV1q0iKnZoLD","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor history points away from larger tables, IF instruction predecode, RAS/victim state, delayed updates, weaker hysteresis, and aggressive update filtering. I’m writing a narrow BTB allocation-policy hypothesis that keeps the proven 16-entry lookup unchanged and only protects resident entries from not-taken alias pollution while still allowing empty-slot learning.","time":{"start":1778675432209,"end":1778675433548},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_08e000062b44a867016a046ee81154819b910e801423ee2b34","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778675448180,"sessionID":"ses_1deb04b20ffeyLsV1q0iKnZoLD","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_rmZ4uI8wagPEQU9QLaYJtxqF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r15s2\n+title: Fill empty BTB slots on not-taken misses\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current compact 16-entry PC-only BTB remains the only predictor shape with a durable win, but prior attempts show that larger tables, narrower tags, victim/RAS state, IF instruction decode, delayed updates, and broad update filtering all cost more than CoreMark repays. The failed taken-only allocation experiment likely protected hot entries but also stopped cold not-taken branches from occupying empty slots and receiving later training, while the current policy lets every not-taken miss evict a resident taken loop entry.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Keep the existing 16-entry direct-mapped BTB lookup, compact tags, word targets, and 2-bit counters unchanged, but refine allocation on update. Matching resident entries should train exactly as today; invalid slots should allocate on any resolved control-flow update, including not-taken conditionals, so cold branches can still be learned; valid mismatched slots should be replaced only by taken updates, leaving the resident entry intact on not-taken alias misses. This preserves broad feedback when capacity is available while avoiding the most damaging not-taken pollution of hot CoreMark loop targets, with no added IF-side decode or lookup state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Refine BTB update allocation so same-tag entries train, invalid slots allocate for taken or not-taken updates, and valid tag-mismatch slots are replaced only by taken updates.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the follo