low update, including not-taken conditionals, so cold branches can still be learned; valid mismatched slots should be replaced only by taken updates, leaving the resident entry intact on not-taken alias misses. This preserves broad feedback when capacity is available while avoiding the most damaging not-taken pollution of hot CoreMark loop targets, with no added IF-side decode or lookup state.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Refine BTB update allocation so same-tag entries train, invalid slots allocate for taken or not-taken updates, and valid tag-mismatch slots are replaced only by taken updates.\"\n","additions":13,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r15s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778675448172,"end":1778675448178}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08e000062b44a867016a046ee97344819b82ed2bad4cb84aa8"}},"id":"prt_e2151404d0026QtBSA0jVIXWLg","sessionID":"ses_1deb04b20ffeyLsV1q0iKnZoLD","messageID":"msg_e215028a600156pRUY5FshDNRR"}}
