{"type":"text","timestamp":1778642812936,"sessionID":"ses_1e0a11099ffeKPZ8ePUp97k4Sg","part":{"id":"prt_e1f5f7f59002EslZonQo2c5mpS","messageID":"msg_e1f5f1d33001r5I0WYbqcdIm01","sessionID":"ses_1e0a11099ffeKPZ8ePUp97k4Sg","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor history shows the current core already has a 16-entry direct-mapped BTB, while the RAS attempt broke formal. I’m going to propose a lower-risk predictor change: statically predict `JAL` in IF from its immediate and reserve the BTB for conditional branches to reduce BTB pollution and cold jump misses.","time":{"start":1778642812761,"end":1778642812935},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0dfb1950ea31b290016a03ef7cab608199b63d4ac2f51815c2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778642819178,"sessionID":"ses_1e0a11099ffeKPZ8ePUp97k4Sg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_LYUrcLGbRwMiYcEOTz5vVLnl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Predict JAL in fetch\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry direct-mapped BTB improved CoreMark, but its benefit is\n+  limited by aliasing and by storing unconditional jumps that can be predicted\n+  directly from the fetched instruction. CoreMark's small C workload includes\n+  repeated calls and unconditional control transfers, so letting JAL occupy BTB\n+  entries wastes predictor capacity that could be used for conditional loop\n+  branches.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a simple IF-stage static predictor for JAL: when the fetched instruction\n+  opcode is JAL, compute pc plus the J immediate and use that as pred_pc/next_pc\n+  without waiting for an EX-stage BTB update. Keep the existing BTB/BHT path for\n+  conditional branches, and stop inserting plain JAL updates into the BTB so\n+  those entries are not evicted by always-taken direct jumps. This should reduce\n+  cold jump penalties and BTB conflict misses with much less state and formal\n+  complexity than a return address stack.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode fetched JAL instructions, compute their immediate target in IF, and give that static prediction priority after redirects but before the BTB fallback.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the branch predictor only for conditional branches and unresolved indirect jumps, avoiding BTB pollution from direct JAL instructions that IF can predict statically.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Predict JAL in fetch\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry direct-mapped BTB improved CoreMark, but its benefit is\n+  limited by aliasing and by storing unconditional jumps that can be predicted\n+  directly from the fetched instruction. CoreMark's small C workload includes\n+  repeated calls and unconditional control transfers, so letting JAL occupy BTB\n+  entries wastes predictor capacity that could be used for conditional loop\n+  branches.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a simple IF-stage static predictor for JAL: when the fetched instruction\n+  opcode is JAL, compute pc plus the J immediate and use that as pred_pc/next_pc\n+  without waiting for an EX-stage BTB update. Keep the existing BTB/BHT path for\n+  conditional branches, and stop inserting plain JAL updates into the BTB so\n+  those entries are not evicted by always-taken direct jumps. This should reduce\n+  cold jump penalties and BTB conflict misses with much less state and formal\n+  complexity than a return address stack.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode fetched JAL instructions, compute their immediate target in IF, and give that static prediction priority after redirects but before the BTB fallback.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the branch predictor only for conditional branches and unresolved indirect jumps, avoiding BTB pollution from direct JAL instructions that IF can predict statically.\"\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","relativePath":"cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r3s2\n+title: \"Predict JAL in fetch\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry direct-mapped BTB improved CoreMark, but its benefit is\n+  limited by aliasing and by storing unconditional jumps that can be predicted\n+  directly from the fetched instruction. CoreMark's small C workload includes\n+  repeated calls and unconditional control transfers, so letting JAL occupy BTB\n+  entries wastes predictor capacity that could be used for conditional loop\n+  branches.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Add a simple IF-stage static predictor for JAL: when the fetched instruction\n+  opcode is JAL, compute pc plus the J immediate and use that as pred_pc/next_pc\n+  without waiting for an EX-stage BTB update. Keep the existing BTB/BHT path for\n+  conditional branches, and stop inserting plain JAL updates into the BTB so\n+  those entries are not evicted by always-taken direct jumps. This should reduce\n+  cold jump penalties and BTB conflict misses with much less state and formal\n+  complexity than a return address stack.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Predecode fetched JAL instructions, compute their immediate target in IF, and give that static prediction priority after redirects but before the BTB fallback.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Update the branch predictor only for conditional branches and unresolved indirect jumps, avoiding BTB pollution from direct JAL instructions that IF can predict statically.\"\n","additions":26,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r3s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778642819175,"end":1778642819177}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0dfb1950ea31b290016a03ef7cd9d881998320b424a1e56a1a"}},"id":"prt_e1f5f8008001zXHViAnbb0k8Nn","sessionID":"ses_1e0a11099ffeKPZ8ePUp97k4Sg","messageID":"msg_e1f5f1d33001r5I0WYbqcdIm01"}}
