{"type":"text","timestamp":1778646552511,"sessionID":"ses_1e06808eaffeP14x81B3tjekMS","part":{"id":"prt_e1f988df6001ydWp6ZKJSC0Kql","messageID":"msg_e1f98345a001KJ5rhYPReB5cnT","sessionID":"ses_1e06808eaffeP14x81B3tjekMS","type":"text","text":"I’ll write a predictor-policy hypothesis that keeps the existing PC-only BTB fast path but changes allocation so not-taken BTB misses do not evict useful taken targets. This targets aliasing/pollution without adding IF instruction decode.","time":{"start":1778646552054,"end":1778646552509},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_01ea3319ac823638016a03fe17de64819b8fa8a8a824e72c02","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778646558487,"sessionID":"ses_1e06808eaffeP14x81B3tjekMS","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_HzbISWeFfmZavYANyemu9CTN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r4s2\n+title: \"Allocate BTB only on taken misses\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The current 16-entry direct-mapped BTB was the only predictor change that\n+  improved CoreMark, but its gain is limited by aliasing. Every resolved\n+  branch or jump currently installs a tag and target, even when a conditional\n+  branch is not taken. A never-taken or mostly-not-taken conditional branch\n+  predicts the same pc+4 path whether it misses in the BTB or hits a weak/strong\n+  not-taken entry, so allocating those misses can evict useful taken loop and\n+  call targets without improving the next-PC decision.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Change the BTB update policy so an update for the same resident PC still\n+  trains the 2-bit counter in both directions, but an update for a different\n+  PC allocates/replaces the entry only when the resolved control-flow was\n+  taken. On not-taken misses, leave the current entry untouched. This keeps\n+  the IF lookup path PC-only and avoids the fetch-stage instruction decode\n+  that hurt the JAL predictor attempt, while reducing direct-mapped BTB\n+  pollution from forward conditionals and cold not-taken branches in CoreMark.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Modify BTB update allocation so matching entries continue to train, taken misses allocate/replace, and not-taken misses leave the existing entry intact.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r4s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tourna