{"type":"text","timestamp":1778649145590,"sessionID":"ses_1e040db50ffexyXDpRosXL3pJb","part":{"id":"prt_e1fc0207d001bMujZKcBeEDpei","messageID":"msg_e1fbf9746001EI7VSPi27B7jPj","sessionID":"ses_1e040db50ffexyXDpRosXL3pJb","type":"text","text":"I’m writing a single predictor-focused YAML: enlarge the existing PC-only direct-mapped BTB from 16 to 32 entries, preserving the current counter semantics and avoiding the failed IF instruction-predecode paths.","time":{"start":1778649145469,"end":1778649145589},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0332deae2878f13f016a04083960b8819b9ef9ccfeba4d7650","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778649149644,"sessionID":"ses_1e040db50ffexyXDpRosXL3pJb","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_lDMn8exhd6wWyVD1f8EzfGyy","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r5s2\n+title: \"Double PC-only BTB capacity\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The only successful predictor change so far was the small direct-mapped BTB,\n+  and the lessons point to aliasing as the remaining limiter. Attempts that\n+  added fetched-instruction predecode, return-stack speculation, or more update\n+  policy control hurt timing or formal tractability. A capacity-only BTB change\n+  keeps the predictor lookup PC-only while reducing conflicts among CoreMark's\n+  repeated loop branches and calls.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Increase the existing direct-mapped BTB/BHT from 16 entries to 32 entries by\n+  widening the PC index by one bit, while preserving the current full-PC tag,\n+  target, 2-bit counter, EX-stage update, and prediction-mismatch recovery\n+  behavior. This should reduce destructive aliasing without adding instruction\n+  decode, extra ways, a RAS, or additional control-flow compares to the fetch\n+  next-PC path. The expected benefit is mainly higher CoreMark iterations per\n+  cycle from fewer warm-loop redirects, with modest Fmax risk from the slightly\n+  larger indexed predictor arrays.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Change the BTB entry count and index width from 16/4 to 32/5, leaving the existing PC-only lookup and EX update semantics intact.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r5s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experime