{"type":"text","timestamp":1778654509451,"sessionID":"ses_1dfef2d61ffeP65ImCxXYnNqeR","part":{"id":"prt_e2011f812001NIe4vl3zxQqRMe","messageID":"msg_e2010fb0b002sJ5HpYnCtHV1Zk","sessionID":"ses_1dfef2d61ffeP65ImCxXYnNqeR","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor wins were the original small BTB and the compact full-entropy tag representation; the losses were bigger tables, IF instruction predecode, RAS complexity, taken-only allocation with counters, and over-narrow tags. I’m going to write a predictor hypothesis that keeps the PC-only 16-entry structure but simplifies the direction state instead of adding capacity or decode.","time":{"start":1778654509074,"end":1778654509448},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_053a8117054847c1016a041d2cc3688199ae9809abf16fc3e4","phase":"commentary"}}}}
