ade a small amount of hysteresis for better Fmax.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Replace the BTB's 2-bit saturating counters with a one-bit direction bit while\n+  keeping the existing 16-entry direct-mapped tag and word-target arrays. Predict\n+  a BTB hit only when the resident direction bit is set, allocate or set the bit\n+  on taken updates, and clear it on matching not-taken updates without allocating\n+  not-taken misses. This preserves the PC-only IF lookup and avoids the failed\n+  larger-table, RAS, and IF-instruction-predecode directions, while removing the\n+  counter add/sub/compare logic and one prediction-state bit per entry from the\n+  front-end predictor cone.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 1\n+  confidence: low\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Replace the 2-bit BTB/BHT counters with one-bit direction state, update it on matching outcomes, allocate only taken misses, and use hit-and-direction for the predicted next PC.\"\n","additions":27,"deletions":0}],"diagnostics":{},"truncated":false},"title":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r7s2.yaml","time":{"start":1778654521104,"end":1778654521105}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f9d6e8af6cf02de016a041d327390819b80dc6b4ce6a227fe"}},"id":"prt_e20120d78001eV1mvpK4ghEWI4","sessionID":"ses_1dfef2d61ffeP65ImCxXYnNqeR","messageID":"msg_e2011fbff0014PajoKvM96Qv2D"}}
