{"type":"text","timestamp":1778656653981,"sessionID":"ses_1dfce69c2ffeVn2I95Ba5u2Sa5","part":{"id":"prt_e2032b1810028ub3xIJ77VJ27J","messageID":"msg_e2031f906001rUYQ8JEqOOibFI","sessionID":"ses_1dfce69c2ffeVn2I95Ba5u2Sa5","type":"text","text":"I’m writing the hypothesis as an EX-update filter: keep the proven IF lookup unchanged, but stop allocating/training the tiny BTB on forward or not-taken conditional branches so loop/backedge entries and direct jumps face less direct-mapped pollution.","time":{"start":1778656653697,"end":1778656653980},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0f9c28d26707841e016a04258d91d08198ae46b5f100db9493","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778656659034,"sessionID":"ses_1dfce69c2ffeVn2I95Ba5u2Sa5","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_OjmdQABzTMZBqO1S87RS3A7y","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Filter BTB updates to loop backedges\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has consistently helped CoreMark. Recent predictor\n+  regressions came from adding IF-side instruction predecode, larger tables,\n+  narrower tags, taken-only allocation logic in the IF update path, and weaker\n+  direction hysteresis. The remaining low-risk opportunity is to preserve the\n+  proven IF lookup path while reducing direct-mapped pollution from conditional\n+  branches that do not help hot loop prediction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Gate branch predictor updates in EX so conditional branches allocate/train the\n+  BTB only when they are taken backward branches, while direct jumps and JALR\n+  continue to update as today. This keeps the fetch critical path, table size,\n+  tag width, target representation, and 2-bit counter lookup unchanged, but stops\n+  forward conditionals and not-taken branches from replacing useful CoreMark loop\n+  backedge entries. Loop exits still recover through the existing EX redirect,\n+  and the sticky backedge entries should improve iterations per cycle under the\n+  random iStall model without repeating the failed larger-table or IF-predecode\n+  approaches.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Qualify bpu_update_valid so conditional branch updates are emitted only for taken backward branches, while jump updates keep the current target-training behavior.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Keep the 16-entry compact-tag BTB lookup unchanged; only rely on the filtered EX update stream, with no new IF-side decode or table capacity changes.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r8s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,29 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r8s2\n+title: \"Filter BTB updates to loop backedges\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has consistently helped CoreMark. Recent predictor\n+  regressions came from adding IF-side instruction predecode, larger tables,\n+  narrower tags, taken-only allocation logic in the IF update path, and weaker\n+  direction hysteresis. The remaining low-risk opportunity is to preserve the\n+  proven IF lookup path while reducing direct-mapped pollution from conditional\n+  branches that do not help hot loop prediction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Gate branch predictor updates in EX so conditional branches allocate/train the\n+  BTB only when they are taken backward branches, while direct jumps and JALR\n+  continue to update as today. This keeps the fetch critical path, table size,\n+  tag width, target representation, and 2-bit counter lookup unchanged, but stops\n+  forward conditionals and not-taken branches from replacing useful CoreMark loop\n+  backedge entries. Loop exits still recover through the existing EX redirect,\n+