{"type":"text","timestamp":1778660018682,"sessionID":"ses_1df9bf59dffezVQaq35rR70eb4","part":{"id":"prt_e2065ff66001FnBgsC1QqFo5wn","messageID":"msg_e2064664d002W5doA2H7j0FLYW","sessionID":"ses_1df9bf59dffezVQaq35rR70eb4","type":"text","text":"The prior predictor history favors preserving the existing 16-entry PC-only BTB policy and trimming representation/metadata instead of adding capacity, IF predecode, RAS, or update filtering. I’ll write a low-risk predictor hypothesis that compresses the predicted-next-PC metadata carried through IF/ID and ID/EX to aligned word form, leaving behavior unchanged while reducing front-end/EX compare routing.","time":{"start":1778660015974,"end":1778660018681},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d1e9d9e7f95310e016a0432afd7f0819b896d5fd2763e4f4d","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778660042876,"sessionID":"ses_1df9bf59dffezVQaq35rR70eb4","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_XB8OGYrFIZ9ULAYe2XMtknke","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Compress predicted PC metadata\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has reliably helped this core. Recent predictor\n+  regressions came from changing policy, capacity, or adding IF-side instruction\n+  decode. One remaining predictor-specific cost is that IF carries a full 32-bit\n+  predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX, then EX compares it against the\n+  resolved aligned next PC on every valid instruction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Store and pipeline the predicted next PC as an aligned word address rather\n+  than a full byte address. The IF predictor already produces only aligned\n+  sequential or BTB targets, and EX suppresses misaligned control transfers by\n+  trapping and using pc+4, so the low two predicted bits are redundant. Changing\n+  pred_pc to pred_pc_word in the pipeline bundles and comparing actual_next_pc[31:2]\n+  in EX preserves BTB behavior and redirect recovery while trimming two carried\n+  bits and a little compare/mux fanout from the predictor validation path.\n+expected_impact:\n+  fitness_delta_pct: 2\n+  confidence: medium\n+changes:\n+  - file: rtl/core_pkg.sv\n+    description: \"Replace if_id_t/id_ex_t pred_pc with a 30-bit aligned predicted PC word field.\"\n+  - file: rtl/if_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Generate predicted_pc_word from the existing sequential/BTB prediction and reconstruct byte PCs only where needed for fetch.\"\n+  - file: rtl/id_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Propagate the predicted PC word through ID/EX without changing decode or RVFI source fields.\"\n+  - file: rtl/ex_stage.sv\n+    description: \"Validate predictions by comparing actual_next_pc[31:2] against the predicted PC word while preserving redirect target semantics.\"\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n+++ /Users/bonetto/bonetto/auto-arch-tournament/.claude/bench-runs/gpt-5_5_high-rep2/cores/bench/experiments/hypotheses/hyp-20260513-003-r9s2.yaml\n@@ -0,0 +1,30 @@\n+id: hyp-20260513-003-r9s2\n+title: \"Compress predicted PC metadata\"\n+category: predictor\n+motivation: |\n+  The existing 16-entry PC-only BTB with compact tags and 2-bit counters is the\n+  only predictor shape that has reliably helped this core. Recent predictor\n+  regressions came from changing policy, capacity, or adding IF-side instruction\n+  decode. One remaining predictor-specific cost is that IF carries a full 32-bit\n+  predicted next PC through IF/ID and ID/EX, then EX compares it against the\n+  resolved aligned next PC on every valid instruction.\n+hypothesis: |\n+  Store and pipeline the predicted next PC as an aligned word address rather\n+  than a full byte address. The IF predictor already produces only aligned\n+  sequential or BTB targets, and EX suppresses misaligned control transfers by\n+  trapping and using pc+4, so the low two predicted bits are redundant. Changing\n+  pred_pc to pred_pc_word in the pipeline bundles and comparing actual_next_pc[31:2]\n+  in EX preserves BTB behavior and redirect recovery while trimming two carried\n+  bits and a little compare/mux fanout from the predicto